1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:16,149
<i>Today, we will have a battle</i>

2
00:00:16,216 --> 00:00:20,153
<i>between the returning chefs</i>
<i>and the challenging chefs.</i>

3
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:23,890
<i>Chef Lee Yeon-bok</i>
<i>versus Chef Lee Mi-yeong.</i>

4
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:28,061
Does it taste good enough
to give energy to Tak?

5
00:00:28,128 --> 00:00:29,162
It's too salty!

6
00:00:29,229 --> 00:00:30,797
IT'S TOO SALTY!

7
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:32,999
It's a bit sweet!

8
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:35,769
Which one did Youngtak choose?

9
00:00:35,835 --> 00:00:37,604
LEE YEON-BOK WINS

10
00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:40,940
Lee Yeon-bok! Chef Lee Yeon-bok wins!

11
00:00:41,007 --> 00:00:42,776
RETURNING CHEFS 1 : 0 NEW CHEFS

12
00:00:42,842 --> 00:00:44,044
This round is a battle

13
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:48,415
between the two hottest chefs
born in the same year.

14
00:00:48,481 --> 00:00:52,218
When I was younger,
my family didn't have enough money.

15
00:00:52,285 --> 00:00:56,456
So we always had rice, raw egg,
and soy sauce.

16
00:00:56,523 --> 00:00:58,425
It's not Edward,

17
00:00:58,491 --> 00:00:59,893
but Eggward.

18
00:00:59,959 --> 00:01:03,563
Choi Hyun-suk makes meringue!

19
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:05,365
The Egg Is on Fire.

20
00:01:05,432 --> 00:01:07,700
Edward Lee only uses the yolks.

21
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,869
He's only using the yolk.

22
00:01:09,936 --> 00:01:11,738
The omelet batter goes in.

23
00:01:11,805 --> 00:01:13,706
-Did it work?
-Like that?

24
00:01:15,675 --> 00:01:17,444
Stop! Time him now.

25
00:01:17,510 --> 00:01:19,946
Please stop for a minute.

26
00:01:21,681 --> 00:01:23,883
EDWARD GETS A FACIAL FOR 1 MINUTE
TO PLAY FAIR

27
00:01:24,684 --> 00:01:26,286
HYUN-SUK LOSES BOTH COOLNESS
AND LAUGHTER

28
00:01:26,352 --> 00:01:28,655
Three. Two. One.

29
00:01:28,721 --> 00:01:31,291
You can start now.

30
00:01:32,492 --> 00:01:35,095
I'm doing all kinds of jobs.

31
00:01:35,161 --> 00:01:37,897
There's a fire. Things are chaotic.

32
00:01:37,964 --> 00:01:40,500
You have 40 seconds left.

33
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:42,302
If you're done first,
you can press the buzzer.

34
00:01:42,368 --> 00:01:44,704
I knew you'd be rushed
when you put on the mask.

35
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,706
You were too relaxed, right?

36
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:48,608
-Chef Hyun-suk is done!
-Chef Hyun-suk is done.

37
00:01:48,675 --> 00:01:51,177
-When did he finish?
-What did you do? You're done?

38
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:55,682
We're now waiting for Edward Lee.

39
00:01:55,748 --> 00:01:58,952
-Edward Lee.
-He's topping it with an egg.

40
00:01:59,018 --> 00:02:01,754
The yolk broke!

41
00:02:01,821 --> 00:02:02,989
MOUTH COVERED

42
00:02:04,357 --> 00:02:06,559
-He failed.
-Fifteen seconds.

43
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:07,861
-Fifteen seconds.
-Fifteen seconds.

44
00:02:07,927 --> 00:02:10,029
-Ten seconds.
-Ten seconds.

45
00:02:10,096 --> 00:02:12,832
-Ten. Nine. Eight.
-Nine. Eight.

46
00:02:12,899 --> 00:02:15,768
-Seven. Six. Five.
-Seven. Six. Five.

47
00:02:15,835 --> 00:02:17,637
-The bell!
-Four. Three.

48
00:02:17,704 --> 00:02:20,273
-Two.
-He's done!

49
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:25,211
-Gosh, this is crazy.
-Edward is finished too.

50
00:02:25,278 --> 00:02:27,547
Hey, wait a moment.

51
00:02:27,614 --> 00:02:30,950
-What a splendid match.
-That's right.

52
00:02:31,017 --> 00:02:33,887
The dishes are finished.
Good work, both of you.

53
00:02:34,554 --> 00:02:36,656
-Time flew by.
-Great work!

54
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:40,693
THE TWO FRIENDS
BATTLED PASSIONATELY

55
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,562
I have a bit of reasonable doubt.

56
00:02:42,629 --> 00:02:45,231
-Chef Hyun-suk, are you really finished?
-Yes, I'm done.

57
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:47,867
It doesn't look finished.

58
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:51,471
The omelet looks
somewhat urgently put together.

59
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:53,072
It may look that way,

60
00:02:53,139 --> 00:02:56,109
but you must keep an eye on a chef's dish
until the moment it's served.

61
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:57,544
EYES SHUT WATCHING
SHOW-OFF CHEF AT WORK

62
00:02:57,610 --> 00:03:01,447
-Whoa, I see. You worked hard on that.
-My gosh.

63
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:03,716
Yes, he put in a lot of work
into that sauce.

64
00:03:03,783 --> 00:03:05,718
-The colors.
-Does it still look unfinished?

65
00:03:05,785 --> 00:03:07,453
-I see.
-No, it looks different.

66
00:03:09,322 --> 00:03:13,593
A RENDEZVOUS
OF CREAMY GOLDEN SAUCE AND OMELET

67
00:03:14,093 --> 00:03:15,728
It changed completely.

68
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:17,497
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S THE EGG
IS ON FIRE

69
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:20,099
Please show us the cross section.

70
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:21,334
It looks soft.

71
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:22,702
What's inside?

72
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:26,606
-There's the yolk.
-That looks crazy.

73
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:28,174
-It looks good.
-The yolk.

74
00:03:28,241 --> 00:03:29,576
-There's a yolk.
-On purpose.

75
00:03:29,642 --> 00:03:34,781
He put in an uncooked yolk inside
and covered it with the batter.

76
00:03:34,847 --> 00:03:37,116
He made it so that the yolk will break.

77
00:03:37,183 --> 00:03:39,886
Hyun-suk seems different
as soon as we cut this up.

78
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:42,088
-I'll use a spoon.
-Will the egg be on fire?

79
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:43,856
A classy egg dish.

80
00:03:43,923 --> 00:03:45,091
Thank you for the food!

81
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:48,094
Will he have a taste of paradise?

82
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:50,563
-It must be good.
-It must be.

83
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,398
HE CAN'T HIDE HIS BLISS

84
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,668
Do you hear the angelic voices?

85
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:58,137
Are you hearing the angels sing?

86
00:03:58,705 --> 00:03:59,839
He can't lie.

87
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,308
-What was so good?
-He looks confident.

88
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:04,077
-What is…
-Why were you shocked?

89
00:04:04,143 --> 00:04:08,047
-I think it's the sauce.
-What am I chewing on the inside?

90
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:11,551
-Crab meat and oysters.
-I see.

91
00:04:11,618 --> 00:04:14,053
I was sure
you probably had normal eggs often,

92
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:17,423
so I made meringue
to make the texture soft.

93
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:22,095
Then, I added the yolk in perfect timing
so when you cut it, the yolk will pop too.

94
00:04:22,161 --> 00:04:24,897
I turned egg in hell into egg in paradise.

95
00:04:24,964 --> 00:04:26,165
-I see.
-But inside that,

96
00:04:26,232 --> 00:04:28,067
there's the sea.

97
00:04:28,134 --> 00:04:30,970
-There's the sea in there?
-Inside the egg.

98
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,839
It's not the Korean sea.

99
00:04:32,905 --> 00:04:34,774
-It's not the Korean sea?
-The Mediterranean?

100
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:36,909
-California?
-The Mediterranean?

101
00:04:36,976 --> 00:04:38,978
-It's overseas.
-Overseas.

102
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:41,814
-It reminds me of Pattaya.
-Pattaya?

103
00:04:41,881 --> 00:04:43,416
It tasted like Pattaya.

104
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:45,118
It's so good.

105
00:04:45,184 --> 00:04:46,552
-I want a bite, too.
-Me too.

106
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:48,354
CURIOUS OF THE PATTAYA SEA TASTE

107
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:51,557
They're all mixed up on the inside.

108
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:53,493
-Like this.
-Like that.

109
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:56,596
A SPIRAL OF TASTY INGREDIENTS

110
00:04:56,663 --> 00:04:59,165
-They're all dancing.
-He makes great expressions.

111
00:04:59,232 --> 00:05:01,034
The sea in Pattaya.

112
00:05:02,068 --> 00:05:05,672
LIKE THE STAIRWAY TO HEAVEN,

113
00:05:05,738 --> 00:05:08,541
THERE ARE LAYERS
AND LAYERS OF FLAVOR

114
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:12,645
CHEF EDWARD'S EGGWARD LEE

115
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:17,383
Let's move on to my friend, Kyun,
whose skin looks replenished.

116
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:19,285
-He has great skin.
-Yes.

117
00:05:19,352 --> 00:05:22,121
EVEN THE ORIGINAL
PRETTY BOY APPROVES

118
00:05:22,188 --> 00:05:24,490
-The pretty boy, Kyun.
-Kyun.

119
00:05:24,557 --> 00:05:26,192
How should he eat this?

120
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:31,431
Eat everything together,
the rice, the egg, and the oyster,

121
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:34,000
-all of them.
-Eat everything together.

122
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:37,070
-Gosh.
-He put <i>chogochujang</i> inside.

123
00:05:37,136 --> 00:05:39,072
-Yes, he used <i>chogochujang</i>.
-He did.

124
00:05:39,138 --> 00:05:41,474
I had a taste of <i>chogochujang</i>,
and it was spectacular.

125
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,443
The <i>chogochujang</i> made by his mom.

126
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:44,777
WHAT DOES EGGWARD LEE TASTE LIKE?

127
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:48,748
TAKING A BIG BITE

128
00:05:49,649 --> 00:05:51,484
NERVOUS

129
00:05:51,551 --> 00:05:53,586
He had a bite.

130
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:56,456
Are you seeing paradise?
His eyes are closed.

131
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:57,724
CAN HE TASTE PARADISE?

132
00:05:57,790 --> 00:05:59,759
Are the angels harking?

133
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,295
Whoa, there's a cloud.

134
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,731
-There is a cloud. He made a cloud.
-He's good.

135
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:07,166
-He arrived.
-Yes, there was a cloud.

136
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,869
-He did make a cloud with the meringue.
-Yes, right. The meringue.

137
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:11,871
Yes, he made meringue for the dish.

138
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:14,140
-It was in the middle.
-Everything was intentional.

139
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,708
-And the rice.
-The rice.

140
00:06:15,775 --> 00:06:17,643
It tastes like scorched rice.

141
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:19,412
-I see.
-He grilled the rice.

142
00:06:19,479 --> 00:06:22,081
-He grilled it?
-He grilled it on the pan.

143
00:06:22,148 --> 00:06:24,384
And between scorched rice and the cloud,

144
00:06:24,984 --> 00:06:26,619
my mom's there.

145
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:30,089
It sounds like he's sharing a dream.

146
00:06:30,156 --> 00:06:33,092
-Your mom's ingredient must be there.
-There was <i>chogochujang</i>.

147
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:35,661
-Is it because of <i>chogochujang</i>?
-<i>Chogochujang</i>.

148
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:38,030
The cloud must've made an impression.

149
00:06:38,097 --> 00:06:39,399
When I had a bite of the cloud…

150
00:06:39,465 --> 00:06:40,433
It must've been soft.

151
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:44,003
It felt like my mother was
holding me and singing a lullaby.

152
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:45,171
-Gosh.
-I can't believe it.

153
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:48,174
-He met his mom in the dream.
-In the dream.

154
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:50,276
-She's alive.
-She is?

155
00:06:50,343 --> 00:06:52,044
She's perfectly alive.

156
00:06:52,111 --> 00:06:53,312
DON'T GET HIM WRONG

157
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:56,816
She's alive,
but came to see you in your dream.

158
00:06:56,883 --> 00:06:58,418
-Let's have a taste too.
-Yes.

159
00:06:58,484 --> 00:07:02,088
This is
Chef Hyun-suk's The Egg Is on Fire.

160
00:07:02,155 --> 00:07:03,289
Isn't it wonderful?

161
00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:05,658
HIS FACE ALREADY SHOWS
HOW DELICIOUS IT IS

162
00:07:05,725 --> 00:07:07,627
It's the sea overseas, right? Not Korean.

163
00:07:07,693 --> 00:07:09,529
Yes, it's definitely not Korean.

164
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:14,400
The stir-fried crab meat and oysters
inside the meringue batter

165
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:18,204
gives some texture after the softness
as the first impression.

166
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:20,440
The flavor burst out in my mouth.

167
00:07:20,506 --> 00:07:23,176
I really thought it was

168
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:26,546
a sly way of cooking.

169
00:07:27,413 --> 00:07:29,148
It was so sly.

170
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:30,750
He's so sly!

171
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:34,754
It was so good that
I wanted to call this cheating.

172
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:38,458
Let's have a taste of Chef Edward's dish.

173
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:40,460
What's this?

174
00:07:40,526 --> 00:07:41,961
-Oyster?
-Oyster.

175
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:44,163
YUM

176
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:48,367
The oyster tastes like
it died in happiness.

177
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:51,270
-It must've died happily.
-It died happily?

178
00:07:51,337 --> 00:07:53,439
The taste of the oyster
lingers in my mouth.

179
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:56,209
Chef Edward has

180
00:07:56,275 --> 00:08:00,012
exotic ways of combining ingredients.

181
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:04,350
I don't think an ordinary Korean chef
could've had this idea.

182
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:07,687
He has a unique way
of building his dishes.

183
00:08:07,753 --> 00:08:09,589
You're right. Yes.

184
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:12,859
Chef Hyun-suk was like a student
who scores high on tests.

185
00:08:12,925 --> 00:08:16,229
-He knows exactly how to win points.
-Yes, he does.

186
00:08:16,295 --> 00:08:19,131
But Edward Lee told us about this dish

187
00:08:19,198 --> 00:08:20,633
-before he made it, right?
-Yes.

188
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,002
-He told us about the egg and rice.
-Yes, right. The story.

189
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:24,871
-If you think about that…
-There's a connection.

190
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:27,707
It reminds you
of your hometown and your mother.

191
00:08:27,773 --> 00:08:28,608
You're right.

192
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:33,579
And he topped it with <i>chogochujang</i>
to complete his story.

193
00:08:33,646 --> 00:08:37,083
Chef Edward, what did you think
about Chef Hyun-suk's dish?

194
00:08:37,149 --> 00:08:38,818
It was so delicious.

195
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:42,188
Yes.

196
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:46,559
A sly technician.

197
00:08:46,626 --> 00:08:48,828
-A sly technician.
-Sly?

198
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:50,496
Edward the storyteller.

199
00:08:50,563 --> 00:08:53,733
Hyun-suk the sly technician.

200
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:58,504
Between the two chefs,
which dish do you want to choose?

201
00:08:58,571 --> 00:08:59,939
Youngtak made his choice.

202
00:09:00,006 --> 00:09:03,142
Gosh, he pressed the button
without hesitating.

203
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:05,745
Who did he choose?

204
00:09:05,811 --> 00:09:08,748
Will it be the utterly sly technician,
Choi Hyun-suk?

205
00:09:08,814 --> 00:09:12,051
Or will it be Chef Edward Lee
who came with a story?

206
00:09:12,118 --> 00:09:14,987
Which dish made Youngtak taste paradise?

207
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:20,192
-Which one did you choose? Who is it?
-Which one?

208
00:09:20,259 --> 00:09:23,396
WHO'S THE WINNER OF THE BIG MATCH
BETWEEN TWO MEN BORN IN 1972?

209
00:09:24,363 --> 00:09:25,631
Who is it?

210
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:27,233
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

211
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:29,402
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK
THE EGG IS ON FIRE WINS

212
00:09:30,036 --> 00:09:31,203
Chef Hyun-suk wins.

213
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,538
YOUNGTAK CHOOSES
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK

214
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:34,507
He chooses Chef Hyun-suk.

215
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:38,678
This means the returning chefs are
still winning.

216
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:42,715
I loved how he came up with the story
to give a taste of my hometown,

217
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:45,284
but in reality,
I meet my mother very often.

218
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:47,420
He was a good son.

219
00:09:47,486 --> 00:09:49,589
You got a taste of her food,
but you saw her yesterday.

220
00:09:49,655 --> 00:09:52,325
The cloud and the rice

221
00:09:52,391 --> 00:09:55,328
all tasted and felt like something
I had never had before.

222
00:09:55,394 --> 00:09:58,898
But my mother was
too mixed up into this dish.

223
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:03,469
We failed to provide information
on his mother.

224
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:07,006
-We didn't know you met her often.
-Exactly.

225
00:10:07,073 --> 00:10:08,808
You can't win against that sly taste.

226
00:10:08,874 --> 00:10:10,509
You can't win against the sly technician.

227
00:10:10,576 --> 00:10:12,378
How do you feel, Edward?

228
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,715
I'm tired.

229
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:18,684
EXHAUSTION CATCHES UP WITH HIM
AFTER THE DEFEAT

230
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:20,586
Exhaustion from traveling surges over him.

231
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:24,724
He may end up snoring
in the green room after this.

232
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:25,691
HE'LL GET A GOOD SLEEP

233
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:27,093
He says he's exhausted.

234
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:29,362
-The dishes were fantastic.
-I see.

235
00:10:29,428 --> 00:10:31,263
Choi Hyun-suk is as good as they say.

236
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:34,367
In order for a chef to capture
the taste of his customers,

237
00:10:34,433 --> 00:10:35,968
he must be sly.

238
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:38,070
HE TRULY IS A SLY TECHNICIAN

239
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:39,271
-Right away.
-He agrees.

240
00:10:39,338 --> 00:10:43,175
Choi Hyun-suk wins against Chef Edward!

241
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:45,411
-He takes his first victory.
-Congratulations.

242
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:46,879
The technician!

243
00:10:49,382 --> 00:10:53,853
Chef Edward was in second place
in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

244
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:56,455
Chef Hyun-suk was eliminated before that.

245
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:00,960
I didn't make up anything.

246
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:03,863
I was so happy for him.
He finally got to win here.

247
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:08,734
Sadly, when it comes to wittiness,
Chef Edward took a complete victory.

248
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:10,469
No matter how hard I try,

249
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:13,005
-I can't win against Kyun.
-I see.

250
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:16,709
-He's a man born for variety shows.
-He's so funny.

251
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:20,446
Not only is he a good chef,
but he also knows how to make it fun.

252
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:23,449
All those things happen as an accident.

253
00:11:25,151 --> 00:11:26,552
I see.

254
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:27,953
-It's just natural.
-I see.

255
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:31,190
He's not trying to stage anything.
It comes naturally.

256
00:11:31,257 --> 00:11:34,026
-Naturally? He's a genius.
-He's a genius.

257
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:35,728
-Funny spoon.
-Funny spoon.

258
00:11:35,795 --> 00:11:38,731
Yes, he has the funny spoon
and the white spoon.

259
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:42,535
-Everyone is laughing but one man.
-Right.

260
00:11:42,601 --> 00:11:45,237
You had a chance
to be the audience, right?

261
00:11:45,304 --> 00:11:46,739
Have you figured everything out?

262
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:51,610
It'd be great if I could
sit and watch until this week.

263
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:53,245
HE BLURTS OUT HIS WISH

264
00:11:53,312 --> 00:11:55,414
No, you have to compete now.

265
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:58,017
-We can't let you do that.
-No.

266
00:11:58,084 --> 00:11:59,418
The production crew said

267
00:11:59,485 --> 00:12:03,222
you asked if we kicked anyone out
during the season.

268
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:04,657
-He wanted to be kicked out?
-Yes.

269
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:07,693
Do you have a rule like
"removal after two unfinished dishes"?

270
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,863
I asked if there was such a rule.

271
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:13,833
I didn't think I could do this,
so I asked them first.

272
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:18,637
I'm not sure if he's trying to be humble.
It's hard for me to figure him out.

273
00:12:18,704 --> 00:12:20,439
He's just pretending.

274
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:22,608
-He's the winner of <i>MasterChef Korea</i>.
-Yes.

275
00:12:22,675 --> 00:12:24,410
That kind of talent won't go anywhere.

276
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:26,445
-We know that.
-Of course.

277
00:12:26,512 --> 00:12:28,247
-First place isn't for just anyone.
-No.

278
00:12:28,314 --> 00:12:30,716
You do have something going on, right?

279
00:12:33,119 --> 00:12:34,220
CAN WE LOOK FORWARD TO IT?

280
00:12:34,286 --> 00:12:35,654
I'm sure he does.

281
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:39,291
Chimchakman, have you watched
<i>Culinary Class Wars</i>?

282
00:12:39,358 --> 00:12:41,360
-Yes, I enjoyed it very much.
-I see.

283
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:42,928
Any memorable moments?

284
00:12:42,995 --> 00:12:45,431
When the judges tried the food
with their eyes covered.

285
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:46,532
-The blind evaluation.
-That was fun.

286
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:50,803
One of these chefs was
the victim of this blind evaluation.

287
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,139
-It was Chef Eun-yeong.
-Chef Eun-yeong.

288
00:12:53,205 --> 00:12:55,875
I heard she was traumatized
after that match.

289
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:58,210
-Was it that bad?
-Was it that bad?

290
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:02,047
During the one-on-one match, I was against
Chef Jung Ji-sun's <i>basi</i> sweet potatoes.

291
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,849
It was a dish I enjoyed and loved making.

292
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:05,417
But after that day,

293
00:13:05,484 --> 00:13:07,686
I haven't eaten or cooked it.

294
00:13:07,753 --> 00:13:10,289
-That can happen.
-What if someone orders it?

295
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:12,158
It traumatized me severely.

296
00:13:12,224 --> 00:13:13,626
-It must've been severe.
-I get it.

297
00:13:14,326 --> 00:13:15,628
COMING RIGHT UP!

298
00:13:15,694 --> 00:13:17,596
I'm reminded of a familiar moment.

299
00:13:18,097 --> 00:13:19,565
It almost killed me.

300
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:22,802
Here we go.

301
00:13:22,868 --> 00:13:24,303
THE RECONSTRUCTION
OF THE NIGHTMARE?

302
00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:26,071
<i>Isn't this</i> basi?

303
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,674
Before we open Chimchakman's fridge,

304
00:13:28,741 --> 00:13:32,244
let us find out his order
and decide on the contenders.

305
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:35,281
What kind of dishes did he order?

306
00:13:35,347 --> 00:13:38,584
This is Chimchakman's order!

307
00:13:39,185 --> 00:13:40,619
Chimchakman's order.

308
00:13:40,686 --> 00:13:42,922
A dish to calm a fatty liver.

309
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:45,925
I was diagnosed
with nonalcoholic fatty liver.

310
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:48,961
-I developed this without drinking.
-It happens.

311
00:13:49,028 --> 00:13:51,330
-My diet was too fatty.
-I see.

312
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:54,099
I'm a seriously picky eater too.

313
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,801
-I see.
-I rarely eat veggies.

314
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:59,138
I wondered if there was
a veggie dish I could enjoy.

315
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:00,806
PONDERING

316
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:02,608
I rarely eat it if it's just as is.

317
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:05,444
But I thought these chefs may have a way.

318
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:06,946
So that was the first order.

319
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:11,383
-A mouthwatering dopamine explosion.
-A mouthwatering dopamine explosion.

320
00:14:12,117 --> 00:14:16,889
I'm an online streamer,
so my life is repetitive.

321
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:18,991
Nothing stimulates me. Nothing's fun.

322
00:14:19,058 --> 00:14:20,192
-No stimulation in life.
-No.

323
00:14:20,259 --> 00:14:23,229
-So I hoped to pick up the joy of dining.
-I see.

324
00:14:23,295 --> 00:14:25,464
-I'm already known for my short appetite.
-Right.

325
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,500
I wanted to eat a dish

326
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:31,637
that'll give me chills
with its maximized strong taste.

327
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:34,406
-I see.
-I especially love dishes made with <i>mala</i>.

328
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:36,842
-You must enjoy spice.
-I do.

329
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:40,646
His name, Chimchakman, means to calm down,
but he wants to be excited.

330
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,748
His name is Chimchakman.

331
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:45,918
Now, there are four chefs left.

332
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:49,121
Jung Ho-young and Kim Poong are left
among the returning chefs.

333
00:14:49,188 --> 00:14:51,957
And new chefs include
Choi Kang-rok and Park Eun-yeong.

334
00:14:52,024 --> 00:14:53,325
Now, Chef Ho-young.

335
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:55,494
I also have a fatty liver,

336
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:59,598
so I already know the ingredients
that are good for your liver.

337
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:03,168
So I'll cook a dish to calm a fatty liver.

338
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:07,506
Then Poong is automatically allocated
to the dish that can excite him.

339
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:09,475
-After all, I am Mr. Dopamine.
-Yes.

340
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:12,011
-Dopamine equals Kim Poong.
-It suits him.

341
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,680
I hope he stays within the line.

342
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:16,081
I worry he'll go overboard.

343
00:15:16,148 --> 00:15:18,617
He'd give us dopamine way over the top.

344
00:15:18,684 --> 00:15:21,153
I've been waiting for this occasion.

345
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:24,023
Because I lost my dopamine hit
after <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> ended.

346
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:28,427
-I'll also explode in dopamine today.
-Will you? Explode it, then!

347
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:31,230
The two chose their fight.
Kim Poong goes there.

348
00:15:31,297 --> 00:15:33,332
You two can pick a spot you want.

349
00:15:33,399 --> 00:15:35,000
TIME FOR THE NEW CHEFS

350
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:36,702
-Go ahead.
-I'll fight

351
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,170
-my upperclassman.
-I see.

352
00:15:38,737 --> 00:15:39,872
I see.

353
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:40,906
The alumni round.

354
00:15:40,973 --> 00:15:43,742
-The upperclassman?
-Yes, I'll fight my upperclassman.

355
00:15:43,809 --> 00:15:45,678
THE FIGHT BETWEEN ALUMNI
OF A PRESTIGIOUS CULINARY SCHOOL

356
00:15:45,744 --> 00:15:47,212
And you don't care about the order?

357
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,714
THE ORDER?

358
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,082
He didn't even look at it.

359
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:53,485
He didn't even look at it,
but he wants to fight Ho-young.

360
00:15:53,552 --> 00:15:56,789
-He just wants to fight his upperclassman.
-He'll get me.

361
00:15:56,855 --> 00:15:58,424
He's here to take your position.

362
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,093
He once took over
his position at the sushi restaurant.

363
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,629
That's not enough.
Give me a spot on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

364
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:05,998
This is a lot of pressure.

365
00:16:06,065 --> 00:16:09,535
-Is that okay, Chef Eun-yeong?
-It's great, actually.

366
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:12,805
Chef Poong said he was
Chef Yeon-bok's student,

367
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:15,341
and I am Chef Lu Chinglai's student.

368
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:19,211
I thought we should fight
as their best pupils.

369
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:21,914
Is that how it goes?

370
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:24,149
That's a lot of pressure on me.

371
00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:26,452
Even my master is here.

372
00:16:26,518 --> 00:16:29,054
He went around saying
he was Chef Yeon-bok's pupil.

373
00:16:30,222 --> 00:16:33,392
Gosh, this is big trouble.
What am I going to do?

374
00:16:33,459 --> 00:16:37,396
In that case,
we decided on the contenders.

375
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:39,264
-The rounds look interesting.
-Okay.

376
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:40,866
Let's go through his fridge.

377
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:42,067
-We should.
-Let's do it.

378
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:43,635
-I look forward to this.
-Let us do it now.

379
00:16:43,702 --> 00:16:46,205
My fridge at home is a built-in,

380
00:16:46,271 --> 00:16:48,307
so I just got what was inside.

381
00:16:48,374 --> 00:16:51,176
CHIMCHAKMAN'S FRIDGE,
COMING RIGHT UP

382
00:16:51,243 --> 00:16:53,445
-You've shared it with us five years ago.
-Yes.

383
00:16:53,512 --> 00:16:56,582
Has the content of your fridge changed?

384
00:16:56,648 --> 00:17:00,953
-Honestly speaking, I don't really know.
-What?

385
00:17:02,988 --> 00:17:05,391
-I rarely open it.
-Is that so?

386
00:17:05,457 --> 00:17:07,626
After all, this is a family fridge.

387
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:08,994
-And he has a child.
-Yes.

388
00:17:09,061 --> 00:17:11,096
-Chef Kang-rok, take a good look.
-Okay.

389
00:17:11,163 --> 00:17:13,065
We present the fridge!

390
00:17:13,132 --> 00:17:15,601
WHAT DOES CHIMCHAKMAN'S FRIDGE
LOOK LIKE?

391
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:18,203
PRESENTING CHIMCHAKMAN'S FRIDGE

392
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:19,405
-It's full.
-Yes.

393
00:17:19,471 --> 00:17:22,074
-Gosh, it's full of stuff.
-It's full.

394
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:24,043
Let's look at the top shelf.

395
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:27,012
Look at this. It's <i>mala</i> sauce.

396
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:30,082
He has something like this. <i>Mala</i> sauce.

397
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:32,618
I work at a Sichuan restaurant
in Hong Kong,

398
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:34,553
so I'm familiar with <i>mala</i>.

399
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:36,121
BAD NEWS

400
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:38,957
-You must toy around with <i>mala</i>.
-Of course.

401
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:40,159
Please use it deliciously.

402
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:43,228
-He has bread.
-I like dinner rolls.

403
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:45,431
-And look. Homemade tofu.
-Homemade tofu?

404
00:17:45,497 --> 00:17:47,499
It would've been fun
to see this last week.

405
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:51,236
There were a few people
who went to tofu hell.

406
00:17:51,303 --> 00:17:52,638
They don't eat tofu anymore.

407
00:17:52,704 --> 00:17:53,872
And I also see

408
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,074
water kimchi.

409
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:57,476
-White kimchi.
-It looks refreshing and delicious.

410
00:17:57,543 --> 00:17:59,378
You should eat something like this.

411
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:01,980
-That one tastes bad.
-Does it?

412
00:18:02,047 --> 00:18:03,749
-Why?
-It's really good.

413
00:18:03,816 --> 00:18:05,384
He doesn't like kimchi.

414
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:07,586
-But I like kimchi stew.
-Kimchi stew.

415
00:18:07,653 --> 00:18:09,488
-Braised kimchi.
-Braised kimchi?

416
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:12,357
Something that tastes strong
with a bit of sugar.

417
00:18:12,424 --> 00:18:15,627
-I see.
-In a nutshell, he's a freaking kid.

418
00:18:15,694 --> 00:18:18,130
Sourness? I like a touch of that.

419
00:18:18,197 --> 00:18:19,865
CONFUSED

420
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:21,934
He's a picky eater.

421
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,002
I see a pot in here.

422
00:18:24,069 --> 00:18:26,705
-It looks cooked.
-It's cabbage doenjang soup.

423
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:28,107
Do you not like stew?

424
00:18:28,173 --> 00:18:30,676
I usually chug everything
after I'm done eating.

425
00:18:30,742 --> 00:18:32,177
HE CHUGS SOUP, NOT BEER

426
00:18:32,244 --> 00:18:35,347
-Do you hold it back?
-I keep forgetting it.

427
00:18:35,414 --> 00:18:36,815
-Like you're taking medicine?
-Come on.

428
00:18:36,882 --> 00:18:39,451
I get too lazy
to switch to a spoon from chopsticks.

429
00:18:39,518 --> 00:18:42,154
You get too lazy
to switch to a spoon from chopsticks?

430
00:18:42,221 --> 00:18:43,555
I do.

431
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:45,791
You have to cook for a guy like this.

432
00:18:45,858 --> 00:18:48,961
-What about these? Salted food.
-Braised eggs.

433
00:18:49,027 --> 00:18:50,729
My wife loves those.

434
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,432
There are fruits in the drawers.
Do you like fruit?

435
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:55,767
I eat it if it's given to me,
but I don't go looking.

436
00:18:55,834 --> 00:18:57,503
There are vegetables next door.

437
00:18:57,569 --> 00:19:01,006
-Potatoes.
-Potatoes. Bean sprouts and mushrooms.

438
00:19:01,073 --> 00:19:03,142
-I think that's cauliflower.
-Cauliflower?

439
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:05,611
-Green onion.
-Gosh.

440
00:19:05,677 --> 00:19:08,046
-Do you like green onion?
-Oh, green onion? I do.

441
00:19:08,113 --> 00:19:09,982
But I don't like green onion kimchi.

442
00:19:10,048 --> 00:19:11,350
You don't like green onion kimchi?

443
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,385
What does he expect us to do?

444
00:19:13,452 --> 00:19:14,553
He got mad.

445
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:16,555
IT'S FUNNY TO SEE HIM SO MAD

446
00:19:16,622 --> 00:19:17,723
On to the freezer.

447
00:19:17,789 --> 00:19:21,326
There is a lot of ice cream
on the first shelf. Do you like ice cream?

448
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:23,428
-My daughter does.
-It's your daughter's.

449
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:28,367
-And I see seafood next door.
-Fish.

450
00:19:28,433 --> 00:19:29,835
-Shrimps.
-Shrimps.

451
00:19:29,902 --> 00:19:31,770
-My daughter likes those.
-Your daughter?

452
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:35,674
That was all for the ingredients
in Chimchakman's fridge.

453
00:19:35,741 --> 00:19:37,142
-Yes.
-Gosh.

454
00:19:37,209 --> 00:19:39,244
I don't get what kind of taste he's into.

455
00:19:39,311 --> 00:19:40,212
-Me too.
-Me too.

456
00:19:40,279 --> 00:19:42,748
He said everything was
for his child and his wife.

457
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:44,516
I actually enjoy <i>gukbap, </i>rice soup,

458
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:46,084
from franchise restaurants.

459
00:19:46,151 --> 00:19:48,120
-Something strong?
-Something fixed.

460
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:51,323
So you don't like it
when your <i>gukbap</i> tastes different?

461
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:54,259
At that point, I may like it or hate it.

462
00:19:54,326 --> 00:19:56,361
What do you expect them to do?

463
00:19:56,428 --> 00:19:58,964
The chefs are confused to death.

464
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:01,433
I definitely like the taste
that I'm familiar with,

465
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:05,137
but new taste is in the realm
of something I may like or not.

466
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,639
Your mustache is bothering me so much.

467
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:10,676
Your mustache is quite annoying.

468
00:20:10,742 --> 00:20:13,078
Chef Edward checks it out too.

469
00:20:13,145 --> 00:20:16,515
So do you like his mustache?

470
00:20:16,582 --> 00:20:20,052
-May I? Yes, I love it.
-He loves it.

471
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:24,056
Wait, it's very…

472
00:20:24,122 --> 00:20:26,792
-May I touch yours?
-Yes, sure.

473
00:20:27,593 --> 00:20:29,027
Wait, it's very…

474
00:20:29,094 --> 00:20:30,796
GULP

475
00:20:32,631 --> 00:20:35,167
-It's very tough.
-Is it?

476
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:38,503
-It's like foxtail.
-Foxtail?

477
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,705
Chef Edward's beard?

478
00:20:39,771 --> 00:20:40,872
It's like foxtail.

479
00:20:40,939 --> 00:20:45,110
