00:30:55,086 --> 00:30:57,722
Jung Ho-young is in shock.

714
00:30:57,789 --> 00:30:59,490
He doesn't like carrots!

715
00:30:59,557 --> 00:31:00,758
He doesn't like carrots.

716
00:31:00,825 --> 00:31:02,861
COUGHING(?)

717
00:31:02,927 --> 00:31:04,395
-Look at him.
-Oh, no.

718
00:31:04,462 --> 00:31:06,731
I heard he has an appetite like a kid.

719
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:09,234
Look at Chef Ho-young. He's choking.

720
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:11,970
-He's suddenly sick.
-He has an appetite like a kid.

721
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:15,206
I don't like carrots,
but he can make it taste delicious.

722
00:31:15,273 --> 00:31:17,809
-So you're fine as long as it's good?
-Yes.

723
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:20,044
He can't pull it out at this point.

724
00:31:20,111 --> 00:31:22,714
-Look at his artistic chopping.
-But I like green onion.

725
00:31:22,780 --> 00:31:24,249
THANKFULLY, HE LIKES GREEN ONION

726
00:31:24,849 --> 00:31:26,751
Did he put them into iced water?

727
00:31:26,818 --> 00:31:28,253
-Yes, iced water.
-Yes.

728
00:31:28,319 --> 00:31:30,355
Why did you soak them in iced water?

729
00:31:30,421 --> 00:31:32,023
I'm trying to reduce the spiciness.

730
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:35,526
He's reducing the spiciness.
Did you learn that at school?

731
00:31:35,593 --> 00:31:37,629
-Yes, I did.
-He learned it at school.

732
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:39,464
I learned it as a first-year.

733
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:41,532
Which professor was it?

734
00:31:41,599 --> 00:31:45,536
-It was Professor Nakamura.
-Nakamura?

735
00:31:45,603 --> 00:31:47,338
-Nakamura?
-Nakamura?

736
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:50,008
Isn't that like John Doe?

737
00:31:50,074 --> 00:31:52,377
Chef Kang-rok, any memorable teachers?

738
00:31:52,443 --> 00:31:55,546
-Oh, yes. Honda.
-Honda?

739
00:31:55,613 --> 00:31:58,149
Honda? Did you say Honda?

740
00:31:58,216 --> 00:32:01,452
-Honda? It's more famous for this.
-These.

741
00:32:03,388 --> 00:32:06,524
Honda versus Nakamura.

742
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:07,492
The two students.

743
00:32:07,558 --> 00:32:09,494
CHUCKLING

744
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:13,097
We're watching cauliflower
turning into steak.

745
00:32:13,164 --> 00:32:15,533
It must be great for your health.

746
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,068
-Anyone can tell.
-Yes.

747
00:32:17,135 --> 00:32:20,271
CAULIFLOWER STEAK!
WITH A SIDE OF MALA SAUCE

748
00:32:20,338 --> 00:32:23,441
6. MIX EGG, FISH SAUCE, MALA,
AND HOT WATER TO MAKE MALA SAUCE

749
00:32:23,508 --> 00:32:28,379
Chef Kang-rok does everything
with so much care.

750
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:30,682
-He's so calm.
-He is. He's very calm.

751
00:32:30,748 --> 00:32:32,250
THE MALA BOTTLE

752
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:33,718
That's the <i>mala</i> sauce.

753
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:37,288
It has everything I like,
both <i>mala</i> and curry.

754
00:32:37,355 --> 00:32:39,457
He adds some <i>mala</i> too.

755
00:32:39,524 --> 00:32:41,659
-What's he making?
-He'll beat the egg.

756
00:32:41,726 --> 00:32:46,331
He's beating the eggs with <i>mala </i>sauce.

757
00:32:46,397 --> 00:32:48,766
-I can't imagine what he'll do.
-Will he cook them?

758
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:50,735
Is that the steak sauce?

759
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:54,205
Yes, he can top it with this later.

760
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:56,574
-It's a side sauce.
-On the side.

761
00:32:56,641 --> 00:32:59,444
He can enjoy it as he likes.

762
00:32:59,510 --> 00:33:01,079
I can pick and choose?

763
00:33:01,145 --> 00:33:05,049
You beat a raw egg and mix it
with soy sauce for sukiyaki, right?

764
00:33:05,116 --> 00:33:08,453
-I think he mixed that with <i>mala</i> sauce.
-I see.

765
00:33:08,519 --> 00:33:09,520
It's the Japanese style.

766
00:33:09,587 --> 00:33:12,590
-I love that sauce.
-I see.

767
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:15,059
This is what he learned
in one of the top three culinary schools.

768
00:33:15,126 --> 00:33:18,429
Chef Kang-rok has finally become
the pride of his alma mater.

769
00:33:18,496 --> 00:33:20,098
When did you learn that in school?

770
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:21,599
He didn't learn this in school.

771
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:23,801
-He just said that.
-I never learned that.

772
00:33:23,868 --> 00:33:26,037
Is he using techniques
you never learned in school?

773
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:27,839
11. MAKE A ROUND BALL
AND DEEP-FRY

774
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:30,008
Chef Ho-young is making balls.

775
00:33:30,074 --> 00:33:31,142
The balls.

776
00:33:31,209 --> 00:33:33,077
THE BASEBALL IS HERE

777
00:33:33,144 --> 00:33:34,579
-He's frying it.
-The baseball.

778
00:33:34,645 --> 00:33:37,949
The carrots look like the seam,
making it similar to a baseball.

779
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:39,350
-You're right.
-It's like the seam.

780
00:33:39,417 --> 00:33:42,987
-Carrots add tasty color to dishes.
-They do.

781
00:33:43,054 --> 00:33:45,356
-It's delicious when it's deep-fried.
-Yes, it is.

782
00:33:45,423 --> 00:33:47,091
You have five minutes now.

783
00:33:47,158 --> 00:33:49,293
-Sung-ju, we're at five minutes!
-Yes?

784
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:50,228
5 MINUTES LEFT

785
00:33:50,294 --> 00:33:52,163
Let me go out and report.

786
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:54,065
-Please check on them.
-You're down to five minutes?

787
00:33:54,132 --> 00:33:55,566
Yes, they're running out of time.

788
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:58,403
I think Chef Kang-rok will dread it,

789
00:33:58,469 --> 00:34:00,338
but I have to do my job.

790
00:34:00,405 --> 00:34:03,174
I must report back
what it's like out here.

791
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:05,043
I'm out here in the studio.

792
00:34:05,109 --> 00:34:07,678
Chef Kang-rok is quite wary of me.

793
00:34:07,745 --> 00:34:11,349
-His lips are perking in and out.
-There's not much time left.

794
00:34:11,416 --> 00:34:12,850
Even my mouth is getting dry.

795
00:34:12,917 --> 00:34:14,385
The cauliflower.

796
00:34:14,452 --> 00:34:18,956
As we speak, he mixes garlic oil
into the sauce.

797
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:23,227
And he's boiling water…
He's double-boiling!

798
00:34:23,294 --> 00:34:26,030
-He's double-boiling.
-He's double-boiling lightly.

799
00:34:26,097 --> 00:34:28,666
I see. Double-boiling.
Why are you doing this?

800
00:34:28,733 --> 00:34:30,868
-Oh, well, yes.
-Doesn't it get cooked?

801
00:34:30,935 --> 00:34:33,271
-I'll tell you later.
-He'll tell us later.

802
00:34:33,337 --> 00:34:35,506
You don't have to talk to me
if you're in a hurry.

803
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:38,910
You steamed these before, right?
May I try this piece?

804
00:34:38,976 --> 00:34:42,080
-It's probably still crunchy.
-Yes, this piece.

805
00:34:42,146 --> 00:34:44,582
Let me check
how cooked the cauliflower is.

806
00:34:44,649 --> 00:34:47,151
CHECKING HOW COOKED
THE CAULIFLOWER IS

807
00:34:47,218 --> 00:34:49,787
Do you feel your fatty liver calming down?

808
00:34:49,854 --> 00:34:51,422
MY FATTY LIVER!

809
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:53,591
It's cooked evenly!

810
00:34:53,658 --> 00:34:57,528
It's cooked evenly!

811
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,231
-The texture.
-It's already good!

812
00:35:00,298 --> 00:35:02,967
-Is it good?
-If you like curry, this will be a hit.

813
00:35:03,034 --> 00:35:05,870
-The subtle taste of curry.
-I love curry.

814
00:35:05,937 --> 00:35:09,440
Chef Kang-rok is looking happier.

815
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:12,710
12. COVER CHOPPED GREEN ONION
WITH STARCH AND FRY

816
00:35:12,777 --> 00:35:15,279
-He's frying those.
-Fried green onion.

817
00:35:15,346 --> 00:35:18,082
That one looks well-done.
It's fried perfectly.

818
00:35:18,149 --> 00:35:19,283
HE'S DONE WITH THE BALLS TOO

819
00:35:19,350 --> 00:35:21,252
WHY IS HE POURING WATER OVER THOSE?

820
00:35:21,319 --> 00:35:23,754
-Why are you pouring hot water?
-What are you doing?

821
00:35:23,821 --> 00:35:25,223
-You fried it!
-He pours hot water over it.

822
00:35:25,289 --> 00:35:28,626
The greasiness won't help his condition,
so I'm taking that out.

823
00:35:28,693 --> 00:35:31,129
HE'S PUTTING IT IN WATER
TO LOSE THE EXTRA GREASE

824
00:35:31,195 --> 00:35:32,396
-The grease.
-It's for the grease.

825
00:35:32,463 --> 00:35:34,765
-Yes.
-Wouldn't it taste a bit too bland?

826
00:35:34,832 --> 00:35:36,033
-No.
-The sauce.

827
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:38,336
In Japanese cuisine,

828
00:35:38,402 --> 00:35:40,705
you often see fried food
eaten in clear soup.

829
00:35:40,771 --> 00:35:42,406
-I've seen them boiled before.
-Yes.

830
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:45,076
TRANSFERRING THE BROTH HE MADE

831
00:35:45,576 --> 00:35:46,477
BUT…

832
00:35:46,544 --> 00:35:49,413
Oh, the mushrooms. The mushrooms. Darn it.

833
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:52,717
I forgot the mushrooms.

834
00:35:53,551 --> 00:35:57,054
-What are you doing with the mushrooms?
-Never mind.

835
00:35:57,121 --> 00:35:58,356
Are you throwing them out?

836
00:35:58,422 --> 00:36:02,260
-I forgot the mushrooms.
-He forgot them.

837
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:03,961
He said, "beep."

838
00:36:07,331 --> 00:36:08,733
EVERYONE IS IN SHOCK

839
00:36:08,799 --> 00:36:10,735
-Are you that mad?
-My gosh.

840
00:36:10,801 --> 00:36:12,937
Please be careful. This is a warning.

841
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:16,407
He didn't say quite that,
but he received a warning.

842
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:18,142
Chef Ho-young, what are you making?

843
00:36:18,209 --> 00:36:21,012
It's the sauce for the balls.

844
00:36:21,078 --> 00:36:23,648
The sauce.
He'll pour this over the tofu balls.

845
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:25,183
The sauce is important.

846
00:36:25,249 --> 00:36:27,385
Let me taste Chef Ho-young's sauce.

847
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:32,290
Does it taste totally clean and witty?

848
00:36:32,857 --> 00:36:36,694
It does taste clean,
but it doesn't seem too witty.

849
00:36:36,761 --> 00:36:38,396
Gosh.

850
00:36:38,462 --> 00:36:40,231
It's just clean.

851
00:36:40,298 --> 00:36:41,966
-Oh, no.
-That's not good.

852
00:36:42,533 --> 00:36:45,903
CHOI KANG-ROK CONTINUES HIS JOURNEY
DESPITE THE CHAOS

853
00:36:46,504 --> 00:36:48,539
HE DOUBLE-BOILS THE BOWL

854
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,641
THEN DROPS IT

855
00:36:51,309 --> 00:36:53,211
GOING BACK TO DOUBLE-BOILING

856
00:36:53,778 --> 00:36:56,047
HE REPEATS THIS INFINITELY

857
00:36:56,113 --> 00:36:58,249
IN THAT TIME,
THE SAUCE BECAME THICK

858
00:36:58,316 --> 00:37:00,084
-Can you taste that, too?
-Which one?

859
00:37:00,151 --> 00:37:02,520
-The sauce he made.
-This one? The sauce!

860
00:37:02,587 --> 00:37:05,590
-May I have a taste of this?
-Yes, of course.

861
00:37:05,656 --> 00:37:07,758
Don't be too wary of me.

862
00:37:07,825 --> 00:37:11,095
I thought it was the raw egg sauce,
but it made it like aioli.

863
00:37:11,162 --> 00:37:12,830
Why are you licking that?

864
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:14,932
-How is it?
-How's the sauce?

865
00:37:14,999 --> 00:37:19,870
Gosh, it's a little bland.

866
00:37:19,937 --> 00:37:22,473
-I'll throw in cheese at the end.
-Sorry?

867
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:25,643
-He'll throw in cheese.
-Cheese.

868
00:37:25,710 --> 00:37:27,478
-He'll use cheese later.
-It's under a minute.

869
00:37:27,545 --> 00:37:29,413
-A minute.
-I don't think you have time.

870
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:33,050
-You have 52 seconds, 50 seconds!
-Oh, no.

871
00:37:33,117 --> 00:37:35,486
-This is bad!
-Fifty seconds!

872
00:37:35,553 --> 00:37:37,521
Fifty seconds!

873
00:37:37,588 --> 00:37:39,323
-Oh, no.
-This is bad!

874
00:37:39,390 --> 00:37:42,226
Both Choi Kang-rok
and Jung Ho-young are in trouble!

875
00:37:42,293 --> 00:37:45,396
They're now in 40 seconds. Chef Kang-rok!

876
00:37:45,463 --> 00:37:47,465
Chef Ho-young serves his dish.

877
00:37:47,531 --> 00:37:50,835
You only have seconds left right now!

878
00:37:50,901 --> 00:37:52,603
-Serve the food!
-You must serve it!

879
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,105
-Thirty seconds.
-Serve the food!

880
00:37:54,171 --> 00:37:55,339
Thirty seconds.

881
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:57,208
There's nothing more you can do!

882
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:59,110
Thirty seconds!

883
00:37:59,176 --> 00:38:00,911
Thirty seconds!

884
00:38:00,978 --> 00:38:02,380
Thirty seconds!

885
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:06,751
There's nothing more you can do!
Thirty seconds!

886
00:38:06,817 --> 00:38:09,420
-He can't do this.
-They're both done cooking!

887
00:38:09,487 --> 00:38:11,889
Will they finish the dishes?

888
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:13,624
-They're done cooking!
-Please hurry.

889
00:38:13,691 --> 00:38:15,726
-Just put it on the dish.
-Serve it!

890
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:17,261
-Twenty seconds.
-Twenty seconds.

891
00:38:17,328 --> 00:38:19,430
WALKING UP IN WORRY

892
00:38:19,497 --> 00:38:22,166
CROWDED

893
00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:24,602
Chef Kang-rok serves the food on a dish.

894
00:38:24,669 --> 00:38:26,737
-He puts it on a dish.
-That looks insane.

895
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:28,472
-It smells good!
-Yes.

896
00:38:28,539 --> 00:38:30,141
-It smells good.
-The cauliflower steak.

897
00:38:30,741 --> 00:38:32,677
Yes.

898
00:38:32,743 --> 00:38:34,512
-Eight! Seven!
-Eight!

899
00:38:34,578 --> 00:38:36,280
-Six!
-Six!

900
00:38:36,347 --> 00:38:37,915
WRAPPING UP
WITH FRIED GREEN ONION

901
00:38:37,982 --> 00:38:40,184
-Five. Four.
-Five. Four.

902
00:38:40,251 --> 00:38:43,087
-Three. Two. One.
-Cheese.

903
00:38:43,154 --> 00:38:45,756
-Two. One.
-Cheese.

904
00:38:45,823 --> 00:38:47,825
-Adding the cheese!
-Cheese!

905
00:38:47,892 --> 00:38:49,093
Time's up!

906
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,628
-The bell.
-The bell.

907
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:52,630
Chef Ho-young finishes first.

908
00:38:52,697 --> 00:38:55,599
-What is he adding?
-Black pepper.

909
00:38:55,666 --> 00:38:59,136
Choi Kang-rok! That's all.

910
00:39:00,304 --> 00:39:02,773
-They spent the entire 15 minutes.
-Time flies.

911
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:06,010
You were able to move quickly
toward the end.

912
00:39:06,077 --> 00:39:08,412
He began to move faster toward the end.

913
00:39:08,479 --> 00:39:11,349
-He could always move fast.
-He could do it quickly.

914
00:39:11,415 --> 00:39:12,717
FITTING FOR THE 15-MINUTE UNIVERSE

915
00:39:13,551 --> 00:39:15,419
These look amazing.

916
00:39:15,486 --> 00:39:17,488
It smells amazing.

917
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:19,790
-It smells so good.
-I want to try it.

918
00:39:20,358 --> 00:39:21,959
-It looks good.
-I knew it.

919
00:39:22,026 --> 00:39:23,227
SNIFFING

920
00:39:23,294 --> 00:39:25,096
-It looks so complete.
-It looks so good.

921
00:39:25,162 --> 00:39:28,899
During the break, Chef Mi-yeong

922
00:39:28,966 --> 00:39:32,303
suddenly came up to me and said,
"Don't be a picky eater."

923
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:34,972
THE PICKY EATER POLICE

924
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:37,441
She talked to me
like I was a kid in a kindergarten.

925
00:39:37,508 --> 00:39:39,944
-She worked in a school.
-She's the Master of School Meals.

926
00:39:40,010 --> 00:39:42,646
-"You must eat everything."
-She's concerned.

927
00:39:42,713 --> 00:39:45,416
So I said,
"Yes, I'll eat everything from now on."

928
00:39:45,483 --> 00:39:47,885
I'll use these dishes as a turning point

929
00:39:47,952 --> 00:39:51,155
to eat more balanced meals from now on.

930
00:39:52,690 --> 00:39:55,359
The tofu balls are as big as a baseball.

931
00:39:55,426 --> 00:39:57,695
-And he fried green onion.
-He did.

932
00:39:57,762 --> 00:39:59,764
TOPPED WITH CRUNCHY GREEN ONION
TO ADD TEXTURE

933
00:40:00,431 --> 00:40:03,100
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S TCWT BALLS

934
00:40:03,167 --> 00:40:06,637
The tofu ball should come apart
if you use a spoon on it.

935
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:10,508
So drench it in the sauce
and eat it in a bite.

936
00:40:10,574 --> 00:40:13,043
He's trying the TCWT Balls.

937
00:40:15,846 --> 00:40:19,650
I hope his fatty liver turns calm. Whoa.

938
00:40:19,717 --> 00:40:22,119
-He means it.
-He does.

939
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:24,655
The sauce is the kick.

940
00:40:24,722 --> 00:40:26,223
-The sauce is the kick?
-The kick.

941
00:40:27,591 --> 00:40:29,860
-He's even eating the carrots.
-He can eat it.

942
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:31,762
-He said he didn't like it.
-No.

943
00:40:31,829 --> 00:40:33,564
I can't taste the carrots.

944
00:40:33,631 --> 00:40:34,832
YOU'RE EATING EVERYTHING

945
00:40:34,899 --> 00:40:39,236
The sauce is sweet yet nutty.

946
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:42,540
And it goes down so smoothly.
I like that kind of texture.

947
00:40:42,606 --> 00:40:46,677
-I see.
-A guy with a fatty liver knows what's up.

948
00:40:46,744 --> 00:40:48,679
-He said he had fatty liver too.
-Yes.

949
00:40:48,746 --> 00:40:50,281
Because he had fatty liver.

950
00:40:50,347 --> 00:40:53,017
-He knew what was good for me.
-Right.

951
00:40:53,083 --> 00:40:54,485
My body is craving this.

952
00:40:54,552 --> 00:40:56,487
-Do you feel a bit healed?
-Yes.

953
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:59,890
He did try to get rid of the grease,
but does it feel greasy?

954
00:40:59,957 --> 00:41:01,592
-Not at all.
-No?

955
00:41:01,659 --> 00:41:04,361
-Doesn't it feel greasy?
-It doesn't taste like fried.

956
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:06,997
-I see.
-Even the carrot is good.

957
00:41:07,064 --> 00:41:10,167
-You aren't even picking it out.
-No, it's really good.

958
00:41:10,234 --> 00:41:11,936
Why are you holding a spoon?

959
00:41:12,002 --> 00:41:14,271
Well, he was enjoying it alone.

960
00:41:14,338 --> 00:41:17,308
KYUN WANTED A TASTE TOO

961
00:41:18,075 --> 00:41:19,710
COME ON, KYUN

962
00:41:19,777 --> 00:41:22,246
-Edward.
-My gosh.

963
00:41:22,313 --> 00:41:23,814
WHY NOT?

964
00:41:23,881 --> 00:41:26,684
-I've never seen a chef stealing a bite.
-No.

965
00:41:26,750 --> 00:41:29,487
He took a quick nap before, right?

966
00:41:29,553 --> 00:41:31,055
He must be hungry now that he's up.

967
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:33,023
IT WAS ABOUT TIME HE GOT HUNGRY

968
00:41:33,090 --> 00:41:35,092
I'M HUNGRY

969
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:36,227
How is it?

970
00:41:36,293 --> 00:41:38,395
-It's good.
-Is it? Is it all right?

971
00:41:38,462 --> 00:41:41,165
But it's a little sweet.

972
00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:43,367
-Just a bit.
-But I love sweet food.

973
00:41:43,434 --> 00:41:45,503
-It's a bit sweet.
-It was a bit sweet for Edward.

974
00:41:45,569 --> 00:41:49,640
He captured his taste perfectly
because he has the appetite of a kid.

975
00:41:51,408 --> 00:41:52,610
EVENLY COOKED CAULIFLOWER

976
00:41:52,676 --> 00:41:55,880
-Chef Kang-rok's dish, Cauliflower Steak.
-Cauliflower Steak.

977
00:41:55,946 --> 00:41:57,281
Please have a taste.

978
00:41:57,348 --> 00:41:59,116
This won't be an easy fight.

979
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:00,951
Chef Kang-rok, how should he eat this?

980
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:02,720
Well, think of it

981
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:05,222
as the kind of meat you like.

982
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:09,126
-Think of it as meat?
-And use your fork and knife.

983
00:42:09,193 --> 00:42:12,630
Will it help if I eat it
while I say it's meat?

984
00:42:12,696 --> 00:42:16,066
-Well, instead of that…
-Like self-hypnosis?

985
00:42:16,133 --> 00:42:19,470
It's vegetable. It's vegetable in reality.

986
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:21,639
It's vegetable, so just think it?

987
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:23,841
Like meat…

988
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:25,709
Let me take that back.

989
00:42:26,977 --> 00:42:28,946
-He was going on and on.
-Too many people

990
00:42:29,013 --> 00:42:30,948
-looked his way just now.
-Too many?

991
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:33,017
Look at that.

992
00:42:33,083 --> 00:42:36,687
-He's eating steak at an upscale place.
-It's meat.

993
00:42:37,288 --> 00:42:38,522
Cover it in sauce.

994
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:40,724
DIPPING IT IN LOTS OF STEAK SAUCE

995
00:42:40,791 --> 00:42:42,426
Think of it as meat.

996
00:42:42,493 --> 00:42:44,528
A dish to calm his fatty liver.

997
00:42:45,596 --> 00:42:47,331
-How will it be?
-Is it meat?

998
00:42:47,398 --> 00:42:49,199
-It's meat.
-Yes.

999
00:42:49,266 --> 00:42:50,701
Is it cooked evenly?

1000
00:42:50,768 --> 00:42:53,337
It's totally vegetable.

1001
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:54,605
OH…

1002
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:57,241
So it wasn't meat at all?

1003
00:42:57,308 --> 00:43:00,544
-It was totally vegetable.
-It was vegetable.

1004
00:43:01,478 --> 00:43:04,381
-But it's delicious veggie.
-Delicious veggie?

1005
00:43:04,448 --> 00:43:06,417
You aren't saying it's not good.

1006
00:43:06,483 --> 00:43:08,185
-It's just not meat.
-It's not meat.

1007
00:43:08,252 --> 00:43:09,887
He doesn't do empty talk.

1008
00:43:09,954 --> 00:43:11,889
How's the texture of the cauliflower?

1009
00:43:11,956 --> 00:43:15,059
I personally like my food a little softer.

1010
00:43:15,125 --> 00:43:16,827
But the crunchy texture isn't bad.

1011
00:43:16,894 --> 00:43:18,262
RELIEVED

1012
00:43:18,329 --> 00:43:22,933
Chef Ho-young's dish was
made perfectly to my taste.

1013
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,735
But Chef Kang-rok's dish

1014
00:43:24,802 --> 00:43:29,273
wasn't really my taste,
but I found out I could like

1015
00:43:29,340 --> 00:43:33,978
a different kind of taste
and texture in food.

1016
00:43:34,044 --> 00:43:36,814
I can also taste <i>mala</i> and curry,

1017
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:40,284
in this dish, but they aren't acting up.

1018
00:43:40,351 --> 00:43:41,619
They're within the line.

1019
00:43:41,685 --> 00:43:44,021
-They're standing far away.
-Just watching?

1020
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:46,223
It feels like Chef Kang-rok.

1021
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:49,460
They do their thing
and stand two steps back.

1022
00:43:49,526 --> 00:43:52,196
Those two don't like to be noticed.

1023
00:43:52,262 --> 00:43:56,100
-But your eyes keep getting drawn to it.
-I see.

1024
00:43:56,166 --> 00:43:58,902
-That's what happens with Chef Kang-rok.
-Yes.

1025
00:43:58,969 --> 00:44:01,538
-You keep looking at him.
-Yes.

1026
00:44:01,605 --> 00:44:03,607
Chef Edward.

1027
00:44:03,674 --> 00:44:05,376
If you want some, have a bite.

1028
00:44:06,377 --> 00:44:07,745
-He grabs a knife.
-The sauce.

1029
00:44:07,811 --> 00:44:10,080
-Sauce.
-Sauce.

1030
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:17,287
-Is it all right?
-Yes, it's all right.

1031
00:44:17,354 --> 00:44:19,323
He's definitely awake now.

1032
00:44:19,390 --> 00:44:21,525
A TASTE THAT KILLS JET LAGS

1033
00:44:21,592 --> 00:44:23,227
It's so hard to choose.

1034
00:44:23,293 --> 00:44:27,197
Chef Kang-rok, you managed
to make something in 15 minutes.

1035
00:44:27,264 --> 00:44:29,233
How do you feel now?

1036
00:44:29,299 --> 00:44:32,636
Well, I feel like
my health just went downhill.

1037
00:44:35,105 --> 00:44:37,841
You tried to look after
another man's health

1038
00:44:37,908 --> 00:44:39,510
and ruined your own?

1039
00:44:39,576 --> 00:44:40,577
Yes, right here.

1040
00:44:40,644 --> 00:44:43,013
Did this side receive lots of stress?

1041
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,682
He did that for another man's liver.

1042
00:44:44,748 --> 00:44:45,916
Look at them.

1043
00:44:45,983 --> 00:44:47,685
-Both of them.
-He just coughed.

1044
00:44:47,751 --> 00:44:49,920
Why don't we have a bite too?

1045
00:44:49,987 --> 00:44:53,424
Let's have a bite of TCWT Balls.

1046
00:44:55,259 --> 00:44:58,028
The sauce is almost like Chinese.

1047
00:44:58,762 --> 00:45:01,065
-Chinese cuisine, like hot and sour soup.
-Yes.

1048
00:45:01,131 --> 00:45:03,067
It almost tastes Chinese.

1049
00:45:03,133 --> 00:45:05,302
It tastes healthy.

1050
00:45:05,369 --> 00:45:08,172
It's a very nutritious dish,

1051
00:45:08,238 --> 00:45:11,909
and children would also enjoy it.

1052
00:45:11,975 --> 00:45:14,311
-Even kids would love it.
-Yes.

1053
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:19,416
The sauce is somewhere in between
the crab soup and the hot and sour soup.

1054
00:45:19,483 --> 00:45:22,352
It tastes a little sour too.

1055
00:45:22,419 --> 00:45:27,725
It's quite similar to how you drop an egg
into crab soup or hot and sour soup.

1056
00:45:27,791 --> 00:45:29,827
Did you learn this
while studying Japanese cuisine?

1057
00:45:29,893 --> 00:45:33,130
-I did, in the 2nd semester, 2nd year.
-The 2nd semester, 2nd year.

1058
00:45:33,197 --> 00:45:35,332
-It was the 2nd semester, 2nd year?
-It was exactly then.

1059
00:45:35,399 --> 00:45:38,769
-Chef Kang-rok must've learned it too.
-Yes.

1060
00:45:38,836 --> 00:45:41,338
When did he cook all this?

1061
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:42,873
YOU'RE SO COOL

1062
00:45:42,940 --> 00:45:43,941
He also had the same time.

1063
00:45:44,007 --> 00:45:45,776
THAT'S MY UPPERCLASSMAN

1064
00:45:45,843 --> 00:45:48,712
Chef Kang-rok's Cauliflower Steak.

1065
00:45:49,179 --> 00:45:50,180
Gosh.

1066
00:45:50,781 --> 00:45:52,850
-My gosh. What is this?
-It's good.

1067
00:45:52,916 --> 00:45:56,086
The cauliflower is
a perfect mix with the sauce.

1068
00:45:56,153 --> 00:45:57,521
It tastes classy.

1069
00:45:57,588 --> 00:45:59,656
-It's a great mix.
-Yes.

1070
00:45:59,723 --> 00:46:02,226
Some cook cauliflower until it's soft,

1071
00:46:02,292 --> 00:46:04,928
and others keep it crunchy like this.

1072
00:46:04,995 --> 00:46:06,864
I loved this texture.

1073
00:46:06,930 --> 00:46:09,700
Curry and <i>mala</i> are a great combo.

1074
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:14,905
I was also inspired
to make something out of this dish.

1075
00:46:14,972 --> 00:46:16,106
-Is that so?
-Yes.

1076
00:46:16,173 --> 00:46:18,609
Whose dish did you enjoy more?

1077
00:46:18,675 --> 00:46:22,646
The one you like is the answer.

1078
00:46:22,713 --> 00:46:24,481
-He's torn.
-It's not easy.

1079
00:46:24,548 --> 00:46:27,718
I want to see his liver
and see how much better it is.

1080
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:30,053
WHICH DISH MADE HIS LIVER CALMER?

1081
00:46:30,554 --> 00:46:34,992
Professor Nakamura's student,
Chef Jung Ho-young.

1082
00:46:35,058 --> 00:46:39,062
And Professor Honda's student,
Chef Choi Kang-rok.

1083
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:41,965
-Gosh.
-The professors' honor is at stake.

1084
00:46:42,032 --> 00:46:45,435
Press one for Jung Ho-young,
two for Choi Kang-rok.

1085
00:46:45,502 --> 00:46:47,871
Please press the button!

1086
00:46:47,938 --> 00:46:49,706
-I did.
-He pressed it.

1087
00:46:49,773 --> 00:46:51,942
Let's find out the result!

1088
00:46:52,009 --> 00:46:56,213
Jung Ho-young, the upperclassman
versus Choi Kang-rok, the underclassman.

1089
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:58,515
Who's the winner of this battle?

1090
00:46:58,582 --> 00:47:02,486
Which dish made
Chimchakman's liver calmer?

1091
00:47:02,553 --> 00:47:04,254
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

1092
00:47:04,321 --> 00:47:05,722
JUNG HO-YOUNG'S TCWT BALLS WINS

1093
00:47:05,789 --> 00:47:07,524
Jung Ho-young wins!

1094
00:47:07,591 --> 00:47:08,859
KEEPING HIS PRIDE
AS AN UPPERCLASSMAN

1095
00:47:08,926 --> 00:47:10,060
The upperclassman won.

1096
00:47:10,127 --> 00:47:15,399
Chef Ho-young wins against Chef Kang-rok
and becomes the winner.

1097
00:47:15,465 --> 00:47:17,367
Everything was delicious,

1098
00:47:17,434 --> 00:47:18,569
but the man

1099
00:47:18,635 --> 00:47:22,639
who has a fatty liver knows
the kind of taste we like.

1100
00:47:22,706 --> 00:47:24,808
-Fatty liver knows fatty liver.
-Yes.

1101
00:47:24,875 --> 00:47:26,810
-Empathy.
-Empathy.

1102
00:47:26,877 --> 00:47:29,680
I didn't know
my fatty liver would be so helpful.

1103
00:47:29,746 --> 00:47:31,315
SPECIAL THANKS TO MY FATTY LIVER

1104
00:47:31,381 --> 00:47:35,485
-He was grateful for his fatty liver.
-He was.

1105
00:47:35,552 --> 00:47:38,589
Chef Kang-rok, you did your best, though.

1106
00:47:38,655 --> 00:47:42,359
Do you think you didn't win
because it wasn't a braised dish?

1107
00:47:42,426 --> 00:47:44,795
-I'll stick to braises from now on.
-Braises.

1108
00:47:44,862 --> 00:47:45,963
I'd be able to do it.

1109
00:47:46,029 --> 00:47:51,001
-Chef Kang-rok was the Braise Man.
-The Braise Man?

1110
00:47:51,068 --> 00:47:52,636
-He should make braises.
-Yes.

1111
00:47:52,703 --> 00:47:55,138
Chimchakman, please put a star on him.

1112
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:56,940
A MEANINGFUL FIRST STAR
FROM A FELLOW FATTY LIVER PATIENT

1113
00:47:57,007 --> 00:47:59,309
He kept his pride up
as the returning chef.

1114
00:47:59,376 --> 00:48:02,279
Jung Ho-young takes his first win!

1115
00:48:04,214 --> 00:48:11,054
THE RECIPE FOR TCWT BALLS
BY CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG

1116
00:48:11,121 --> 00:48:13,390
Next round,

1117
00:48:13,457 --> 00:48:18,228
a mouthwatering dopamine explosion
using Chimchakman's ingredients.

1118
00:48:18,295 --> 00:48:22,399
Starting from last week,
we played three rounds so far.

1119
00:48:22,466 --> 00:48:24,968
The current score is three to zero,

1120
00:48:25,035 --> 00:48:29,239
with an overwhelming win
by the returning chefs.

1121
00:48:29,306 --> 00:48:32,042
We only have one more round to go.

1122
00:48:32,109 --> 00:48:35,412
I feel awful
that Team Culinary Class Wars is

1123
00:48:35,479 --> 00:48:36,980
getting wiped out in these battles.

1124
00:48:37,047 --> 00:48:40,584
I'll make sure I win this round
and seize this point.

1125
00:48:40,651 --> 00:48:42,152
Hey, I'm sorry.

1126
00:48:42,219 --> 00:48:44,621
One chef of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i> has won.

1127
00:48:45,188 --> 00:48:46,490
WAIT, IS HE SAYING…

1128
00:48:47,090 --> 00:48:48,625
THAT'S ME

1129
00:48:49,893 --> 00:48:51,895
The sly technician.

1130
00:48:51,962 --> 00:48:55,699
If the sly technician was with you,
you could've won a point.

1131
00:48:55,766 --> 00:48:57,434
TAKING THIS SIDE AND THAT SIDE

1132
00:48:57,501 --> 00:49:00,103
I'm looking forward to this round.

1133
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:04,141
This is a battle between best pupils
of master Chinese cuisine chefs.

1134
00:49:04,207 --> 00:49:06,043
My goodness.

1135
00:49:06,109 --> 00:49:09,046
This is a battle of pride

1136
00:49:09,112 --> 00:49:13,050
for both Chef Lee Yeon-bok sitting here
as well as for Chef Lu Chinglai.

1137
00:49:13,116 --> 00:49:14,952
-Isn't that so?
-Yes.

1138
00:49:15,018 --> 00:49:17,020
When it comes to Chinese cuisine,

1139
00:49:17,087 --> 00:49:19,556
there are two chefs,
Lu Chinglai and Lee Yeon-bok.

1140
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:22,459
-Yes.
-You're saying that yourself?

1141
00:49:22,526 --> 00:49:25,429
In that case, if Poong loses,

1142
00:49:25,495 --> 00:49:27,698
will it also mean your loss?

1143
00:49:27,764 --> 00:49:29,833
If he loses, will you return the star?

1144
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:31,868
It's not that serious.

1145
00:49:31,935 --> 00:49:34,871
-Hey, what did I do wrong?
-I'm sorry.

1146
00:49:34,938 --> 00:49:37,040
-I'm sorry.
-All he ever did was teach him.

1147
00:49:37,107 --> 00:49:39,176
He's going to be the judge.

1148
00:49:39,242 --> 00:49:40,811
Don't worry.

1149
00:49:40,877 --> 00:49:42,512
That's not going to happen.

1150
00:49:43,714 --> 00:49:46,149
The two are already on fire.

1151
00:49:46,216 --> 00:49:48,452
Did Chef Lu Chinglai give you any tips?

1152
00:49:48,518 --> 00:49:52,189
He said the two hosts will come near
and try to harass me a lot,

1153
00:49:52,255 --> 00:49:55,559
-so I shouldn't lose my focus.
-I see.

1154
00:49:55,625 --> 00:49:56,860
I don't think Chef Lu Chinglai expected

1155
00:49:56,927 --> 00:50:00,197
-she'd end up fighting me.
-Right.

1156
00:50:00,263 --> 00:50:01,898
I will also disturb her.

1157
00:50:01,965 --> 00:50:03,367
-Yes.
-You're right.

1158
00:50:03,433 --> 00:50:06,837
If you win this round,
will you challenge Chef Yeon-bok too?

1159
00:50:06,903 --> 00:50:09,473
If I win today,
I think it'll be worth a try.

1160
00:50:10,640 --> 00:50:14,945
-He's a stepping stone to Chef Yeon-bok.
-A stepping stone.

1161
00:50:15,012 --> 00:50:20,150
Other new chefs continued to lose
because they haven't adapted yet.

1162
00:50:20,217 --> 00:50:21,318
Chef Eun-yeong, what are you doing

1163
00:50:21,385 --> 00:50:23,320
-instead of standing there?
-What is it?

1164
00:50:23,387 --> 00:50:26,690
I have to keep my hands cold,
so let me ice them.

1165
00:50:26,757 --> 00:50:28,058
WHAT IS SHE MAKING?

1166
00:50:28,125 --> 00:50:28,959
-Wait.
-To cook?

1167
00:50:29,026 --> 00:50:31,128
Why does she need to keep her hands cold?

1168
00:50:31,194 --> 00:50:32,596
He's warming his hands up.

1169
00:50:33,964 --> 00:50:36,199
I have to keep my hands warm.

1170
00:50:36,266 --> 00:50:37,601
Yes.

1171
00:50:37,667 --> 00:50:40,504
-It's fire versus ice.
-Yes.

1172
00:50:41,338 --> 00:50:43,440
WEBTOON ARTIST
KIM POONG'S INGREDIENTS

1173
00:50:43,507 --> 00:50:45,642
KIRIMOCHI, MALA SAUCE,
MINCED PORK

1174
00:50:45,709 --> 00:50:47,844
SHRIMP, MALA PASTE, POTATOES

1175
00:50:47,911 --> 00:50:49,880
The dish I'm making is called

1176
00:50:50,747 --> 00:50:53,283
Dopamine Poongly Charged.

1177
00:50:53,350 --> 00:50:55,752
-Dopamine Poongly Charged.
-Dopamine Poongly Charged.

1178
00:50:55,819 --> 00:50:59,623
There's a Chinese dish called
volcano potatoes.

1179
00:50:59,689 --> 00:51:01,558
-Volcano potatoes?
-Volcano potatoes?

1180
00:51:01,625 --> 00:51:03,160
-Like the mountain?
-Volcano?

1181
00:51:03,226 --> 00:51:04,728
Yes, do you know what it is?

1182
00:51:04,795 --> 00:51:05,829
-No.
-You don't.

1183
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:07,664
-I have no idea.
-Chef Yeon-bok doesn't know.

1184
00:51:07,731 --> 00:51:09,466
Even the master doesn't know.

1185
00:51:09,533 --> 00:51:11,101
-Did you make it?
-It's a real dish.

1186
00:51:11,168 --> 00:51:14,471
The world of Chinese cuisine is
both vast and deep.

1187
00:51:16,206 --> 00:51:19,543
It's a dish that
Chinese people make mostly at home.

1188
00:51:19,609 --> 00:51:22,412
It's also easy to make.

1189
00:51:22,479 --> 00:51:25,515
-Volcano potatoes.
-You pile up potatoes like a mountain,

1190
00:51:25,582 --> 00:51:28,251
-make sauce, and pour over it.
-Like a volcano.

1191
00:51:28,318 --> 00:51:31,822
-It's shaped like a volcano.
-An actual volcano.

1192
00:51:31,888 --> 00:51:33,023
Do you like potatoes?

1193
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:34,624
-Yes, I do.
-I'm glad.

1194
00:51:34,691 --> 00:51:35,592
I love fries.

1195
00:51:35,659 --> 00:51:37,594
-Fries.
-Fries? You love fries?

1196
00:51:37,661 --> 00:51:38,762
He said he'd boil them.

1197
00:51:38,829 --> 00:51:40,730
It'd be better if he fried them.

1198
00:51:41,698 --> 00:51:43,800
-Fries.
-Wouldn't that be better?

1199
00:51:43,867 --> 00:51:46,570
Fries are my favorite food.

1200
00:51:46,636 --> 00:51:49,206
I can munch on them forever.

1201
00:51:49,272 --> 00:51:51,274
You should have some backbone as a chef.
Will you change it?

1202
00:51:51,341 --> 00:51:53,243
-I'm not a chef.
-He's not a chef.

1203
00:51:53,310 --> 00:51:55,812
I don't have any backbone,

1204
00:51:55,879 --> 00:51:59,049
but I'll boil them anyway.
This isn't a deep-fried dish.

1205
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:00,784
Artist Poong doesn't have a plan B.

1206
00:52:00,851 --> 00:52:03,253
No, I either fail miserably…

1207
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:05,455
-All or nothing.
-Yes.

1208
00:52:06,289 --> 00:52:08,325
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS

1209
00:52:08,391 --> 00:52:10,460
TANGERINES, PLAIN BREAD, CHEESE,
GRANA PADANO CHEESE, ICE CREAM

1210
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:13,830
I prepared a dish called
Happy <i>Basi</i>-Day.

1211
00:52:13,897 --> 00:52:15,999
-Happy <i>Basi</i>-Day.
-Happy <i>Basi</i>-Day.

1212
00:52:16,066 --> 00:52:17,200
<i>-Basi</i>?
-<i>Basi</i>?

1213
00:52:17,267 --> 00:52:19,469
-I thought you were traumatized.
-<i>Basi</i>?

1214
00:52:19,536 --> 00:52:22,506
I prepared <i>basi</i> ice cream
to overcome my trauma.

1215
00:52:22,572 --> 00:52:24,541
-Ice cream <i>basi</i>?
-Ice cream <i>basi</i>?

1216
00:52:24,608 --> 00:52:28,378
You lost against Chef Jung Ji-sun
by a hair when you made this.

1217
00:52:28,445 --> 00:52:29,846
She's taking it out on Poong.

1218
00:52:29,913 --> 00:52:31,581
Yes, I'm getting my revenge.

1219
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:35,018
I'll cover ice cream with bread,
deep-fry it,

1220
00:52:35,085 --> 00:52:39,422
and also make glaciers next to it
like candy stars.

1221
00:52:39,489 --> 00:52:41,791
When you eat everything,
you'll have a dopamine explosion.

1222
00:52:42,592 --> 00:52:44,461
And you also said you had a sweet tooth.

1223
00:52:44,528 --> 00:52:46,029
It sounds good.

1224
00:52:46,096 --> 00:52:47,197
You'll be touched.

1225
00:52:47,264 --> 00:52:49,499
Iceberg versus volcano.

1226
00:52:49,566 --> 00:52:51,835
-Yes, you're right.
-Water and fire.

1227
00:52:51,902 --> 00:52:55,272
What's important is
if you'll use your perk or not.

1228
00:52:55,338 --> 00:52:56,406
Yes, right.

1229
00:52:56,473 --> 00:52:59,509
Chef Kang-rok boldly gave up his perk

1230
00:52:59,576 --> 00:53:02,846
and ended up suffering a loss.

1231
00:53:02,913 --> 00:53:06,149
But he was so cool.
I wanted to give him a standing ovation.

1232
00:53:06,216 --> 00:53:08,585
-I was greatly touched when I saw him…
-Yes?

1233
00:53:08,652 --> 00:53:10,487
…in the battle without the perk.

1234
00:53:10,554 --> 00:53:11,721
-He's a real chef.
-He's so sly.

1235
00:53:11,788 --> 00:53:13,089
-Isn't he real sly?
-He is.

1236
00:53:15,058 --> 00:53:16,560
During the break,

1237
00:53:16,626 --> 00:53:20,931
he said he always ran out of time.

1238
00:53:20,997 --> 00:53:24,167
So I thought he could keep that going.

1239
00:53:24,234 --> 00:53:26,336
-And?
-I'll stop him for a minute.

1240
00:53:26,403 --> 00:53:28,805
-Stopping for a minute?
-So 14 minutes.

1241
00:53:28,872 --> 00:53:31,474
-This is the worst.
-This is huge.

1242
00:53:31,541 --> 00:53:32,709
It's harder to get stopped.

1243
00:53:32,776 --> 00:53:35,045
One minute will have a huge impact.

1244
00:53:35,111 --> 00:53:36,546
Ms. Goddess, against me?

1245
00:53:36,613 --> 00:53:37,781
I have to win today.

1246
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:40,917
And now, we will begin

1247
00:53:40,984 --> 00:53:45,455
the mouthwatering dopamine explosion round
with Chimchakman's ingredients.

1248
00:53:45,522 --> 00:53:46,823
Wow.

1249
00:53:47,390 --> 00:53:51,161
TENSION FALLS WITH THE DARKNESS

1250
00:53:51,228 --> 00:53:53,363
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong is
here to show her

1251
00:53:53,430 --> 00:53:57,234
the fiery taste of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
with his exploding volcano dish.

1252
00:53:57,300 --> 00:53:59,469
Up against him is Chef Park Eun-yeong,

1253
00:53:59,536 --> 00:54:04,174
who'll make Kim Poong lose his mind
with a dish that gives blood sugar spikes.

1254
00:54:04,241 --> 00:54:08,511
Which one of them will
enjoy the dopamine of their victory?

1255
00:54:08,578 --> 00:54:11,281
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1256
00:54:11,348 --> 00:54:12,549
THE COOK-OFF BEGINS!

1257
00:54:12,616 --> 00:54:13,783
Begin!

1258
00:54:13,850 --> 00:54:16,086
LU CHINGLAI'S PUPIL
VS LEE YEON-BOK'S PUPIL

1259
00:54:16,152 --> 00:54:19,089
BLACK SPOON CHEF
VS COOK IN THE DARKNESS

1260
00:54:19,155 --> 00:54:20,757
The 15 minutes have begun.

1261
00:54:20,824 --> 00:54:23,393
She's going to use
the one-minute stop in the middle.

1262
00:54:23,460 --> 00:54:28,164
When she shouts it out,
Artist Poong must stop.

1263
00:54:28,231 --> 00:54:31,201
-Ice cream <i>basi</i>.
-Yes.

1264
00:54:31,268 --> 00:54:32,802
-I look forward to it.
-Me too.

1265
00:54:32,869 --> 00:54:35,138
There's also another dish
called <i>basi bing</i>.

1266
00:54:35,205 --> 00:54:37,440
-It means fried ice.
-Fried ice.

1267
00:54:37,507 --> 00:54:41,278
There was this odd dish
that literally fried ice.

1268
00:54:41,344 --> 00:54:44,748
-Instead of ice, she's using ice cream.
-Ice cream.

1269
00:54:44,814 --> 00:54:46,483
She's rolling the bread flat.

1270
00:54:46,549 --> 00:54:48,551
She'll wrap ice cream with that.

1271
00:54:48,618 --> 00:54:52,155
She made the bread flat.

1272
00:54:52,222 --> 00:54:55,258
SHE CALMLY WARMS UP THE OIL

1273
00:54:55,325 --> 00:54:58,161
-Artist Poong should cook the potatoes.
-Yes, they need to be cooked.

1274
00:54:58,228 --> 00:55:01,298
He's not putting them in as is.
He just chopped them.

1275
00:55:01,364 --> 00:55:03,833
I just need to cook them quickly.

1276
00:55:04,434 --> 00:55:06,102
They go into a pressure cooker.

1277
00:55:07,304 --> 00:55:08,838
Is it fully closed?

1278
00:55:08,905 --> 00:55:09,973
-It is.
-Okay.

1279
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:12,709
-He looks very anxious on the inside.
-Yes.

1280
00:55:12,776 --> 00:55:15,111
-His posture looks poor too.
-Yes.

1281
00:55:17,447 --> 00:55:18,715
THE CUTTING SKILLS OF DARKNESS

1282
00:55:19,382 --> 00:55:20,283
WHOA!

1283
00:55:21,484 --> 00:55:25,755
-As we speak, he cuts green onion.
-Be more gentle.

1284
00:55:25,822 --> 00:55:28,391
The speed of his knife is faster.

1285
00:55:28,458 --> 00:55:30,327
But his hand should be next to the knife,

1286
00:55:30,393 --> 00:55:33,163
-but it was far away.
-He's scared.

1287
00:55:33,229 --> 00:55:34,631
He might hurt his finger.

1288
00:55:38,768 --> 00:55:42,005
-He makes big sounds, but the size…
-They aren't even.

1289
00:55:42,072 --> 00:55:44,374
I feel anxious seeing him like this.

1290
00:55:44,441 --> 00:55:46,509
He'll destroy everything
in his Chinese knife's way.

1291
00:55:46,576 --> 00:55:48,345
THE PUNCHES OF DARKNESS

1292
00:55:48,411 --> 00:55:49,312
ENERGETIC

1293
00:55:49,379 --> 00:55:53,016
-He's using his hands.
-He uses his hands, not his knife.

1294
00:55:53,083 --> 00:55:54,351
-Whoo!
-Yes.

1295
00:55:54,984 --> 00:55:56,019
Yes.

1296
00:55:56,086 --> 00:55:57,887
SHAKES HEAD

1297
00:55:57,954 --> 00:56:00,023
He's full of dopamine.

1298
00:56:00,790 --> 00:56:03,660
He's full of dopamine.

1299
00:56:03,727 --> 00:56:05,128
That's where the dopamine was?

1300
00:56:05,195 --> 00:56:09,566
He looks clumsy and sloppy,
which makes the chefs feel uneasy.

1301
00:56:09,632 --> 00:56:12,102
EVERY MOVE WAS INTENTIONAL!

1302
00:56:12,168 --> 00:56:15,505
Chef Yeon-bok's best pupil, Kim Poong.
He continuously provokes his opponent.

1303
00:56:15,572 --> 00:56:17,273
-Is he making red pepper oil?
-Red pepper oil.

1304
00:56:17,340 --> 00:56:19,042
He added green onion and garlic.

1305
00:56:19,109 --> 00:56:20,910
He was making red pepper oil.

1306
00:56:21,578 --> 00:56:23,613
-She's slicing ice cream.
-She sliced it.

1307
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:26,015
-She's slicing the entire pint?
-Yes.

1308
00:56:26,082 --> 00:56:28,918
Chef Eun-yeong slices
the entire pint of ice cream.

1309
00:56:28,985 --> 00:56:31,755
-Does she want to use that shape?
-I see.

1310
00:56:31,821 --> 00:56:34,124
-It looks pretty.
-Is she keeping the shape?

1311
00:56:34,190 --> 00:56:36,192
It's shaped like cheese.

1312
00:56:36,259 --> 00:56:37,660
I need more oil.

1313
00:56:37,727 --> 00:56:39,262
Are you making red pepper oil?

1314
00:56:39,329 --> 00:56:41,331
No, it's not red pepper oil.

1315
00:56:42,565 --> 00:56:43,400
WHOOSH!

1316
00:56:44,768 --> 00:56:45,702
DISCIPLINED MOVES!

1317
00:56:45,769 --> 00:56:47,604
STEALING OIL!

1318
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:49,539
You're making a huge scene.

1319
00:56:49,606 --> 00:56:50,807
STEALING

1320
00:56:51,408 --> 00:56:52,842
I GOT YOU!

1321
00:56:52,909 --> 00:56:54,444
THE OIL THIEF
WAS A WEBTOON ARTIST

1322
00:56:54,511 --> 00:56:59,082
He's stealing the opponent's oil!

1323
00:56:59,149 --> 00:57:00,417
-I can't do it like this!
-He stole the oil.

1324
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:02,619
I'm sorry. It was yours!

1325
00:57:02,685 --> 00:57:04,954
I really didn't know.

1326
00:57:05,021 --> 00:57:06,723
It was just sitting there.

1327
00:57:06,790 --> 00:57:07,657
Hey.

1328
00:57:07,724 --> 00:57:09,959
It wasn't red pepper oil.
He's dropping the meat.

1329
00:57:10,026 --> 00:57:12,495
He's just adding it altogether
because he has no time.

1330
00:57:12,562 --> 00:57:15,532
It wasn't red pepper oil.
Also, the pan isn't even hot yet.

1331
00:57:15,598 --> 00:57:16,966
He's not just using the oil.

1332
00:57:17,534 --> 00:57:19,469
PARK EUN-YEONG
SHAPES THE ICE CREAM

1333
00:57:20,770 --> 00:57:25,875
Chef Eun-yeong is using ice cream,
so she should time everything perfectly.

1334
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:27,777
Wouldn't it be a problem
to be done too early?

1335
00:57:27,844 --> 00:57:29,479
-Exactly.
-It would be.

1336
00:57:29,546 --> 00:57:33,016
She kept her hands cold
to stop the ice cream from melting.

1337
00:57:33,082 --> 00:57:36,052
It could melt
because of her body temperature.

1338
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:38,922
2. PUT STARCHY WATER ON THE BREAD
WITH ICE CREAM ON TOP AND COVER

1339
00:57:39,856 --> 00:57:41,558
A ROUND COOKIE CUTTER

1340
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:43,693
SHE SHAPES THE ICE CREAM

1341
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:45,862
AND MAKES IT NEAT WITH A KNIFE

1342
00:57:45,929 --> 00:57:48,531
SHE CALMLY BUILDS HER DISH
TOGETHER…

1343
00:57:49,132 --> 00:57:51,267
THE COOK OF THE DARKNESS IS
IN A FRENZY NEXT TO HER

1344
00:57:51,334 --> 00:57:52,869
Sugar.

1345
00:57:52,936 --> 00:57:54,704
Cooking wine.

1346
00:57:54,771 --> 00:57:56,973
Soy sauce. Cooking wine.

1347
00:57:57,040 --> 00:57:59,943
Cooking wine. Where's the cooking wine?

1348
00:58:00,009 --> 00:58:02,212
It's behind gochujang.

1349
00:58:02,278 --> 00:58:03,313
What's with him?

1350
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:04,981
The bread just ripped.

1351
00:58:05,048 --> 00:58:06,216
Did it rip?

1352
00:58:06,282 --> 00:58:08,051
Yes, I can see the ice cream.

1353
00:58:08,117 --> 00:58:09,285
-Look.
-You're right.

1354
00:58:09,352 --> 00:58:11,254
I can just patch it.

1355
00:58:11,321 --> 00:58:13,723
3. CUT THE BREAD AND ICE CREAM
INTO A CIRCULAR SANDWICH

1356
00:58:13,790 --> 00:58:15,625
She's patching up the ice cream.

1357
00:58:15,692 --> 00:58:18,928
I love ice cream that comes with bread.

1358
00:58:18,995 --> 00:58:20,230
-There are a few.
-Yes.

1359
00:58:20,296 --> 00:58:22,332
-Bbangddoa.
-Bbangddoa.

1360
00:58:22,398 --> 00:58:25,268
The key would be
keeping the ice cream from melting.

1361
00:58:26,369 --> 00:58:28,338
His dish is way too red.

1362
00:58:28,404 --> 00:58:31,341
-It's almost too red and turning black.
-Yes.

1363
00:58:31,407 --> 00:58:32,942
My gosh.

1364
00:58:33,009 --> 00:58:36,312
-What's that?
-<i>Mala </i>sauce.

1365
00:58:36,379 --> 00:58:38,882
My stomach hurts when I eat spicy food,

1366
00:58:38,948 --> 00:58:40,884
so I'm not so good with it.

1367
00:58:40,950 --> 00:58:43,186
-So it can't be too spicy.
-It looks too spicy.

1368
00:58:43,253 --> 00:58:47,056
The color does look too red.
Kim Poong's red flavor.

1369
00:58:47,123 --> 00:58:48,358
HOW ARE THE POTATOES?

1370
00:58:48,424 --> 00:58:50,059
The pressure cooker.

1371
00:58:50,126 --> 00:58:53,029
It'll burn if he's stopped
just before he pulls it out.

1372
00:58:53,096 --> 00:58:54,397
I see.

1373
00:58:55,131 --> 00:58:58,868
Will Chef Eun-yeong
take that into consideration?

1374
00:58:58,935 --> 00:59:01,638
She will, because we just said it.

1375
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:02,839
Do you think so?

1376
00:59:02,906 --> 00:59:04,674
You have 8 minutes and 30 seconds.

1377
00:59:04,741 --> 00:59:06,209
FINALLY, SUGAR IS IN THE PICTURE

1378
00:59:06,276 --> 00:59:10,680
You have to use it before six minutes
to make him stop for a full minute.

1379
00:59:10,747 --> 00:59:12,181
Why has it been so long?

1380
00:59:12,248 --> 00:59:13,583
You don't have much time left.

1381
00:59:13,650 --> 00:59:15,585
We're about halfway done.

1382
00:59:15,652 --> 00:59:17,587
How can she melt that much sugar quickly?

1383
00:59:17,654 --> 00:59:19,856
-Is that sugar?
-Yes, that's all sugar.

1384
00:59:19,923 --> 00:59:23,126
The chefs are worried
if the sugar would melt in time.

1385
00:59:23,192 --> 00:59:25,295
THIS TIME, POURING FLOUR IN

1386
00:59:25,795 --> 00:59:28,298
What's Chef Eun-yeong doing now?

1387
00:59:28,364 --> 00:59:30,934
-The batter.
-It's the deep-fry batter.

1388
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:34,671
She'll put the ice cream bread
into the batter and deep-fry it.

1389
00:59:34,737 --> 00:59:35,605
She'll fry that?

1390
00:59:35,672 --> 00:59:37,407
Wouldn't the ice cream melt?

1391
00:59:37,473 --> 00:59:39,642
-Of course, it will.
-It's just basic knowledge.

1392
00:59:39,709 --> 00:59:42,312
If you fry it for a short amount of time,
it won't melt.

1393
00:59:42,378 --> 00:59:44,247
What? You can do that?

1394
00:59:44,314 --> 00:59:46,916
When will she stop him for a minute?

1395
00:59:46,983 --> 00:59:48,985
You have 7 minutes and 10 seconds or so.

1396
00:59:49,052 --> 00:59:50,420
She doesn't have much left.

1397
00:59:50,486 --> 00:59:52,855
You can't use it anymore
once it passes six minutes.

1398
00:59:52,922 --> 00:59:54,857
You should probably do it soon.

1399
00:59:54,924 --> 00:59:57,093
-She's checking something.
-She is.

1400
00:59:57,160 --> 00:59:59,495
Is it done? Is it time?

1401
00:59:59,562 --> 01:00:02,031
She's keeping an eye
on what Kim Poong is doing.

1402
01:00:02,098 --> 01:00:03,833
WHY? WHAT?

1403
01:00:03,900 --> 01:00:06,502
-Kim Poong began to look too.
-A war of nerves.

1404
01:00:06,569 --> 01:00:10,273
When will she use
the one-minute stop perk?

1405
01:00:10,340 --> 01:00:13,009
Kim Poong holds her in check
to stop her from using it.

1406
01:00:13,076 --> 01:00:15,311
He's glaring at her.

1407
01:00:16,779 --> 01:00:19,549
I think Chef Eun-yeong is
waiting for something.

1408
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:22,185
-Starch water?
-Yes, it's starch water.

1409
01:00:22,251 --> 01:00:23,152
You don't have much left.

1410
01:00:23,219 --> 01:00:24,654
You should stop him soon.

1411
01:00:24,721 --> 01:00:27,023
-Please stop!
-Stop!

1412
01:00:27,090 --> 01:00:28,358
Stop!

1413
01:00:28,424 --> 01:00:30,893
-Kim Poong stops.
-Save the potatoes!

1414
01:00:30,960 --> 01:00:32,428
-Kim Poong.
-The potatoes!

1415
01:00:32,495 --> 01:00:34,864
He doesn't know what to do.

1416
01:00:34,931 --> 01:00:35,999
The sauce.

1417
01:00:36,065 --> 01:00:38,768
He has no choice but to wait.

1418
01:00:38,835 --> 01:00:39,902
My gosh. Come on!

1419
01:00:39,969 --> 01:00:42,005
Can it get boiled down like that?

1420
01:00:42,071 --> 01:00:43,573
The volcano is simmering.

1421
01:00:43,640 --> 01:00:46,242
-I took it out.
-It's not over the fire.

1422
01:00:46,309 --> 01:00:49,212
The volcano continues to boil
even when it's not over the fire.

1423
01:00:49,278 --> 01:00:53,549
Chef Eun-yeong's sugar isn't melting.
She needs it to melt!

1424
01:00:53,616 --> 01:00:55,418
Once it begins to melt, it'll speed up.

1425
01:00:55,485 --> 01:00:57,453
-Is that so?
-It's only slow at first?

1426
01:00:57,520 --> 01:00:59,822
Kim Poong must wait for 30 more seconds.

1427
01:00:59,889 --> 01:01:02,659
-I really have no time.
-You're nearing the five-minute mark.

1428
01:01:02,725 --> 01:01:05,762
-That's sugar?
-Kim Poong has 15 seconds.

1429
01:01:05,828 --> 01:01:07,864
Do not move, Kim Poong.

1430
01:01:07,930 --> 01:01:10,466
-Time truly is relative.
-Yes.

1431
01:01:11,167 --> 01:01:13,803
-It flew by, but it's so slow now.
-Five. Four.

1432
01:01:13,870 --> 01:01:16,773
-Three. Two. One.
-Two. One.

1433
01:01:16,839 --> 01:01:19,242
Kim Poong is free now.

1434
01:01:19,308 --> 01:01:21,411
You have 5 minutes and 10 seconds left.

1435
01:01:22,145 --> 01:01:24,747
Gosh, this is crazy.

1436
01:01:24,814 --> 01:01:26,382
KIRIMOCHI:
JAPANESE GLUTINOUS RICE CAKE,

1437
01:01:26,449 --> 01:01:27,450
USUALLY GRILLED TO TASTE

1438
01:01:28,184 --> 01:01:31,487
The sugar began to melt.

1439
01:01:31,554 --> 01:01:33,589
And now, five minutes.

1440
01:01:33,656 --> 01:01:37,126
-Jung-hwan, please go out there.
-Gosh.

1441
01:01:37,193 --> 01:01:40,963
-It feels like the time is flying now.
-Yes, it flew, stopped, then flew again.

1442
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:42,699
-The sugar looks fast-forwarded.
-Right?

1443
01:01:42,765 --> 01:01:44,801
It'll melt faster once it begins to melt.

1444
01:01:44,867 --> 01:01:47,470
That must be hot.

1445
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:49,639
She's oiling the pan.

1446
01:01:49,706 --> 01:01:52,642
-The sugar is almost fully melted.
-Yes.

1447
01:01:52,709 --> 01:01:54,343
She takes the sugar.

1448
01:01:54,410 --> 01:01:56,312
AND SHE POURS IT OVER ICE?

1449
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:57,914
Hey, what's she doing?

1450
01:01:57,980 --> 01:01:59,515
Whoa, the sugar?

1451
01:02:02,819 --> 01:02:06,589
ARE YOU WATCHING THIS,
JUNG JI-SUN?

1452
01:02:06,656 --> 01:02:08,691
-What's that?
-She poured sugar over ice.

1453
01:02:08,758 --> 01:02:11,627
-I poured sugar over ice.
-Sugar over ice?

1454
01:02:11,694 --> 01:02:14,697
Even that ice looks delicious.

1455
01:02:14,764 --> 01:02:16,265
Why did she do that?

1456
01:02:16,332 --> 01:02:18,868
It'll solidify the sugar instantly.

1457
01:02:18,935 --> 01:02:20,803
-like that.
-I'm so curious.

1458
01:02:20,870 --> 01:02:24,273
-Jung-hwan, try a piece of the sugar.
-Yes?

1459
01:02:24,340 --> 01:02:26,109
It looks like sugar crafting.

1460
01:02:26,175 --> 01:02:30,680
The sugar froze up like a sculpture.

1461
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:33,916
It looks like a sculpture.
I can't believe she did this.

1462
01:02:33,983 --> 01:02:35,451
You have under three minutes.

1463
01:02:35,518 --> 01:02:38,321
Now, this sauce. Let me try this sauce.

1464
01:02:38,387 --> 01:02:39,822
The sauce!

1465
01:02:39,889 --> 01:02:42,992
The sauce. It looks really spicy to us.

1466
01:02:43,059 --> 01:02:47,396
Gosh, this is…
The sauce got separated from the oil.

1467
01:02:47,463 --> 01:02:49,732
Stop poking at it and have a bite!

1468
01:02:50,500 --> 01:02:52,735
It looks really oily and hot.

1469
01:02:52,802 --> 01:02:54,904
-Jung-hwan, gulp it down.
-Yes?

1470
01:02:56,606 --> 01:02:58,074
But there's too much oil.

1471
01:02:58,141 --> 01:02:59,909
Yes, tell us what it tastes like.

1472
01:02:59,976 --> 01:03:03,479
It already smells so pungent
even before I put my mouth on it.

1473
01:03:03,546 --> 01:03:05,381
It may burn your tongue!

1474
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:07,416
HE RELUCTANTLY HAS A BITE
LIKE IT'S MEDICINE

1475
01:03:07,483 --> 01:03:08,651
How is it?

1476
01:03:11,554 --> 01:03:13,856
-It's good.
-It's good?

1477
01:03:13,923 --> 01:03:15,291
Isn't it spicy?

1478
01:03:15,358 --> 01:03:16,826
It's seasoned perfectly.

1479
01:03:16,893 --> 01:03:19,796
You have under two minutes.
About two minutes left.

1480
01:03:19,862 --> 01:03:22,398
THE ICE CREAM SANDWICH

1481
01:03:22,465 --> 01:03:25,268
-She's going to fry the ice cream.
-She'll fry it.

1482
01:03:25,334 --> 01:03:27,570
She's frying it.

1483
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:28,938
What's it like?

1484
01:03:29,005 --> 01:03:31,541
-She's frying it!
-Chef Eun-yeong fries ice cream!

1485
01:03:31,607 --> 01:03:32,642
AND MELTS MORE SUGAR

1486
01:03:32,708 --> 01:03:33,976
The ice cream can't melt!

1487
01:03:34,043 --> 01:03:36,045
-She can do that?
-No, that'd ruin everything.

1488
01:03:36,112 --> 01:03:37,380
How long do you fry it for?

1489
01:03:37,446 --> 01:03:39,715
-Just until it browns.
-Just the color.

1490
01:03:40,983 --> 01:03:42,385
The potatoes.

1491
01:03:42,952 --> 01:03:44,620
OPENED

1492
01:03:44,687 --> 01:03:47,623
Artist Poong's potatoes are ready too.

1493
01:03:47,690 --> 01:03:48,758
It's so hot!

1494
01:03:48,825 --> 01:03:50,059
THE POTATOES POP OUT
WITH A SCREAM

1495
01:03:50,126 --> 01:03:52,728
The potatoes are too mashed.

1496
01:03:52,795 --> 01:03:53,930
That's what I wanted.

1497
01:03:53,996 --> 01:03:55,498
-You did?
-Yes, I have to do this.

1498
01:03:55,565 --> 01:03:58,000
-It's separated from the skin.
-Yes, that's how it's done.

1499
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:00,136
The point of this dish is
how humble it is.

1500
01:04:00,203 --> 01:04:01,604
It's so hot!

1501
01:04:02,238 --> 01:04:03,606
Why is the fire so strong?

1502
01:04:03,673 --> 01:04:06,342
Kim Poong mashes the potatoes.

1503
01:04:06,409 --> 01:04:08,044
He's moving very quickly.

1504
01:04:09,145 --> 01:04:11,948
-He has no time. 1 minute and 30 seconds.
-Yes, 1 minute and 30 seconds.

1505
01:04:12,014 --> 01:04:13,883
He's busy mashing potatoes.

1506
01:04:13,950 --> 01:04:17,119
-So this was what you wanted?
-Yes.

1507
01:04:17,186 --> 01:04:18,955
Aren't you going to use shrimps?

1508
01:04:19,021 --> 01:04:20,056
Right!

1509
01:04:20,122 --> 01:04:22,358
Aren't you going to use shrimps?

1510
01:04:22,425 --> 01:04:25,428
-Right!
-Aren't you going to use shrimps?

1511
01:04:25,494 --> 01:04:28,030
-Shrimps.
-Aren't you going to use shrimps?

1512
01:04:28,097 --> 01:04:29,398
Cook them and throw them in.

1513
01:04:29,465 --> 01:04:30,800
Aren't you going to use shrimps?

1514
01:04:30,867 --> 01:04:33,569
HE HAS NO PLAN B

1515
01:04:34,804 --> 01:04:36,739
He forgot about it!

1516
01:04:36,806 --> 01:04:38,875
I just saved this guy.

1517
01:04:38,941 --> 01:04:40,843
You need to use the shrimps!

1518
01:04:40,910 --> 01:04:42,778
Argh!

1519
01:04:42,845 --> 01:04:45,781
-It'll cook if you throw them in now.
-Right now.

1520
01:04:45,848 --> 01:04:48,584
Cook it over high heat. It'll get cooked.

1521
01:04:48,651 --> 01:04:50,853
-The shrimps are…
-Yes?

1522
01:04:50,920 --> 01:04:52,655
…still alive and dancing.

1523
01:04:52,722 --> 01:04:55,124
Goodness. It'll jump out.

1524
01:04:55,191 --> 01:04:56,259
FRIED ICE CREAM

1525
01:04:56,826 --> 01:04:58,594
-She has the fry.
-It's hot.

1526
01:04:58,661 --> 01:05:02,298
She says it's hot
as she stir-fries the fry.

1527
01:05:02,365 --> 01:05:04,467
-Are you coating it with sugar?
-She is.

1528
01:05:04,533 --> 01:05:06,435
The melted sugar splattered on her hands.

1529
01:05:06,502 --> 01:05:09,205
-She's moving very quickly.
-Cheese.

1530
01:05:09,272 --> 01:05:10,773
Are you missing anything?

1531
01:05:10,840 --> 01:05:12,408
Everything is perfect.

1532
01:05:12,475 --> 01:05:16,379
Chef Eun-yeong says
everything she did was perfect!

1533
01:05:16,445 --> 01:05:17,947
Thirty seconds!

1534
01:05:18,014 --> 01:05:19,916
You have 30 seconds left.

1535
01:05:19,982 --> 01:05:22,318
You have 30 seconds. Please wrap up.

1536
01:05:22,385 --> 01:05:23,753
You're running out of time!

1537
01:05:23,819 --> 01:05:26,055
Kim Poong shakes his wok around.

1538
01:05:26,122 --> 01:05:27,790
PARK EUN-YEONG
FINISHES THE ICEBERG

1539
01:05:27,857 --> 01:05:30,026
So the potatoes go like this?

1540
01:05:30,092 --> 01:05:33,029
-She's done.
-Chef Eun-yeong is done!

1541
01:05:33,095 --> 01:05:34,263
-She's done!
-She's done!

1542
01:05:34,330 --> 01:05:36,399
Chef Eun-yeong is done.

1543
01:05:36,465 --> 01:05:38,067
-And Kim Poong.
-Ten seconds.

1544
01:05:38,134 --> 01:05:41,170
-Ten. Nine. Eight.
-Nine. Eight.

1545
01:05:41,237 --> 01:05:44,573
-Seven. Six. Five.
-Seven. Six. Five.

1546
01:05:44,640 --> 01:05:48,911
-Four. Three. Two. One.
-Four. Three. Two. One.

1547
01:05:48,978 --> 01:05:50,546
Kim Poong is done!

1548
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:52,481
DOPAMINE POONGLY CHARGED
IS FINISHED

1549
01:05:52,982 --> 01:05:53,950
-My gosh.
-He's done too.

1550
01:05:54,016 --> 01:05:55,484
-That looks good too.
-It does.

1551
01:05:55,551 --> 01:05:57,486
It feels like
watching the Champions League.

1552
01:05:59,555 --> 01:06:01,557
-The process itself is fun.
-Totally.

1553
01:06:01,624 --> 01:06:03,259
Smell it. It's insane.

1554
01:06:03,326 --> 01:06:07,096
-It smells like Sichuan cuisine.
-I see.

1555
01:06:07,163 --> 01:06:09,966
BASI MADE WITH ICE CREAM

1556
01:06:10,800 --> 01:06:12,969
AND SUGAR ICEBERG FOR EXTRA SWEETNESS

1557
01:06:14,203 --> 01:06:18,074
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
HAPPY BASI-DAY

1558
01:06:18,474 --> 01:06:21,610
First of all, Chef Eun-yeong was
traumatized by <i>basi</i> sweet potato.

1559
01:06:21,677 --> 01:06:24,213
-Yes.
-But she'll overcome it with <i>basi</i>.

1560
01:06:24,280 --> 01:06:27,750
She finished a dish called
Happy <i>Basi</i>-Day.

1561
01:06:27,817 --> 01:06:29,385
I'd like to make an offer.

1562
01:06:29,452 --> 01:06:32,855
The mission in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i> was
tasted with a blindfold on the judges.

1563
01:06:32,922 --> 01:06:35,391
Why don't you taste the dishes

1564
01:06:35,458 --> 01:06:37,893
while you're blindfolded?

1565
01:06:37,960 --> 01:06:39,929
-I can do that.
-Is that all right?

1566
01:06:39,996 --> 01:06:41,998
-Here.
-The blindfold.

1567
01:06:42,064 --> 01:06:43,599
I'm reminded of a familiar scene.

1568
01:06:43,666 --> 01:06:45,434
THE MOMENT THAT MADE
PARK EUN-YEONG TREMBLE

1569
01:06:45,501 --> 01:06:46,969
You look cool even when you're covered up.

1570
01:06:47,036 --> 01:06:49,338
-Please hand it over to him.
-He's still handsome.

1571
01:06:49,405 --> 01:06:51,040
Chef Edward is helping.

1572
01:06:51,107 --> 01:06:52,675
That dish isn't for you.

1573
01:06:52,742 --> 01:06:53,909
Chef Edward is helping.

1574
01:06:53,976 --> 01:06:56,412
That dish isn't for you.

1575
01:06:56,979 --> 01:06:59,048
HE WAS BORN FUNNY

1576
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:01,517
DISAPPOINTED

1577
01:07:01,584 --> 01:07:03,352
I thought you were awake now.

1578
01:07:03,419 --> 01:07:06,622
-He has his eyes covered.
-Yes.

1579
01:07:06,689 --> 01:07:09,425
Chef Eun-yeong, why don't you
cut a bite and put it in his mouth?

1580
01:07:09,492 --> 01:07:11,160
-Should I do that?
-Wow.

1581
01:07:11,227 --> 01:07:14,430
-Let me feed you.
-The ice cream.

1582
01:07:14,497 --> 01:07:15,931
It's crunchy.

1583
01:07:15,998 --> 01:07:17,033
-Gosh.
-Gosh.

1584
01:07:17,099 --> 01:07:18,634
The ice cream is still there.

1585
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:19,969
I can't see anything.

1586
01:07:20,036 --> 01:07:21,570
-How did she do that?
-It looks good.

1587
01:07:21,637 --> 01:07:23,539
-I thought it'd melt.
-It's a dessert.

1588
01:07:23,606 --> 01:07:26,675
-The chopsticks.
-Should he use a spoon?

1589
01:07:26,742 --> 01:07:27,943
Excuse me.

1590
01:07:28,010 --> 01:07:29,812
PROPPING UP FALLING ICE CREAM

1591
01:07:29,879 --> 01:07:33,215
Kyun, you seem to love
taking part in everything.

1592
01:07:33,949 --> 01:07:37,753
-What time is it in Kentucky?
-It's Washington.

1593
01:07:37,820 --> 01:07:40,089
In Washington, it's now 8 a.m.

1594
01:07:40,156 --> 01:07:42,758
-So it's a good morning.
-Good morning.

1595
01:07:42,825 --> 01:07:44,026
It's time for breakfast.

1596
01:07:44,093 --> 01:07:45,728
A good morning <i>basi</i>.

1597
01:07:45,795 --> 01:07:47,463
-Here it goes.
-Double spoons?

1598
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:51,100
It's in his mouth. Please have a taste.

1599
01:07:51,167 --> 01:07:53,002
It has to taste good.

1600
01:07:53,936 --> 01:07:55,171
DOES IT BURST WITH DOPAMINE?

1601
01:07:55,237 --> 01:07:56,205
Chimchakman.

1602
01:07:56,272 --> 01:07:59,775
He said the taste could dwindle
when he wears a blindfold.

1603
01:07:59,842 --> 01:08:01,911
He said he was unable to tell
what it tastes like.

1604
01:08:02,611 --> 01:08:04,280
-Gosh.
-"Gosh"?

1605
01:08:04,346 --> 01:08:05,748
What does it taste like?

1606
01:08:05,815 --> 01:08:07,716
There was this sugar taffy

1607
01:08:07,783 --> 01:08:09,385
people used to sell
in front of elementary schools.

1608
01:08:09,452 --> 01:08:10,986
-People made shapes.
-The carp.

1609
01:08:11,053 --> 01:08:13,522
-Yes, the carp.
-The sugar candy.

1610
01:08:13,589 --> 01:08:14,857
It tastes like that.

1611
01:08:14,924 --> 01:08:17,126
-It tastes like sugar candy?
-Is that a good thing?

1612
01:08:17,193 --> 01:08:19,095
Is that a good thing?

1613
01:08:19,161 --> 01:08:21,897
-I'm not sure. May I have another bite?
-Another bite.

1614
01:08:21,964 --> 01:08:23,265
-Let me help.
-Sure.

1615
01:08:23,332 --> 01:08:26,902
-The center part.
-The center.

1616
01:08:26,969 --> 01:08:29,371
Chimchakman has his mouth wide opened.

1617
01:08:29,438 --> 01:08:31,474
I think he's getting some dopamine hits.

1618
01:08:31,540 --> 01:08:33,742
Yes, he has his mouth opened wide.

1619
01:08:33,809 --> 01:08:35,711
-Yes.
-He has so many gold teeth.

1620
01:08:35,778 --> 01:08:37,847
You're keeping gold in there?

1621
01:08:37,913 --> 01:08:38,848
He's rich.

1622
01:08:38,914 --> 01:08:40,649
-Here it comes.
-Here it comes.

1623
01:08:40,716 --> 01:08:43,219
HE TRIES THE BASI AGAIN

1624
01:08:43,285 --> 01:08:44,854
It's overflowing.

1625
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:47,089
-I have a piece of tissue.
-Okay.

1626
01:08:47,923 --> 01:08:49,425
-Mmm.
-That was…

1627
01:08:49,492 --> 01:08:52,161
He might like it
because he has an appetite like a kid.

1628
01:08:52,228 --> 01:08:55,898
-Wait, this is so good.
-It's so good?

1629
01:08:55,965 --> 01:08:58,033
Does it have a crunchy outside
and a soft inside?

1630
01:08:58,100 --> 01:08:59,068
The ice cream…

1631
01:08:59,135 --> 01:09:02,238
-Excuse me.
-As we speak, Chef Edward…

1632
01:09:02,304 --> 01:09:03,572
I WAS LOW ON SUGAR

1633
01:09:03,639 --> 01:09:05,441
He steals another piece.

1634
01:09:05,508 --> 01:09:07,009
How is it, Kyun?

1635
01:09:08,110 --> 01:09:10,079
-It's the best.
-It's the best.

1636
01:09:10,145 --> 01:09:12,181
I like ice cream, bread,

1637
01:09:12,248 --> 01:09:14,583
and sugar taffy too.

1638
01:09:14,650 --> 01:09:17,119
And everything is here. It's a set.

1639
01:09:17,186 --> 01:09:20,222
Can you break the iced sugar and eat that?

1640
01:09:20,289 --> 01:09:21,590
He can open his eyes for that, right?

1641
01:09:21,657 --> 01:09:23,559
-Yes, you should do that.
-Yes.

1642
01:09:23,626 --> 01:09:24,894
BLINDFOLD OFF

1643
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,529
You can see it with your eyes.

1644
01:09:26,595 --> 01:09:29,798
She made it just like that.
It's like ice crystals.

1645
01:09:29,865 --> 01:09:30,833
Gosh.

1646
01:09:30,900 --> 01:09:33,969
It's definitely more delicious
to eat it while I'm looking at it.

1647
01:09:34,036 --> 01:09:35,571
I think

1648
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:38,140
I just need to live with my fatty liver.

1649
01:09:38,207 --> 01:09:39,642
You must love that a lot.

1650
01:09:39,708 --> 01:09:41,710
He loves it too much.

1651
01:09:41,777 --> 01:09:46,448
-Why don't you let Youngtak try some?
-May I try it?

1652
01:09:47,483 --> 01:09:51,220
IT LOOKS SPICY
AS IF IT'S ABOUT TO BURST

1653
01:09:52,021 --> 01:09:56,325
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
DOPAMINE POONGLY CHARGED

1654
01:09:56,392 --> 01:09:58,794
This time, put the blindfold back on.

1655
01:09:58,861 --> 01:10:01,797
It's still hot,
so you may end up burning yourself.

1656
01:10:01,864 --> 01:10:04,099
-Really?
-I'll deduct points if I get burned.

1657
01:10:04,767 --> 01:10:06,302
PREPARING A BITE
TO AVOID DEDUCTIONS

1658
01:10:06,368 --> 01:10:07,269
Eat it with the potato.

1659
01:10:07,336 --> 01:10:09,805
With the potato.
Yes, there was potato underneath.

1660
01:10:09,872 --> 01:10:11,907
I think I've tried this before.

1661
01:10:11,974 --> 01:10:13,275
Have you made it for me?

1662
01:10:13,342 --> 01:10:16,345
-You probably had it in your dream.
-Really?

1663
01:10:16,412 --> 01:10:18,314
-I hope it's new.
-Wasn't it at your café?

1664
01:10:18,380 --> 01:10:19,748
I didn't.

1665
01:10:19,815 --> 01:10:22,585
How was this, Youngtak?
Please tell us first.

1666
01:10:22,651 --> 01:10:26,055
It tastes really peculiar.
Instead of vegetables

1667
01:10:26,121 --> 01:10:28,123
in a croquette,

1668
01:10:28,190 --> 01:10:30,526
there's ice cream inside.

1669
01:10:31,260 --> 01:10:32,995
OPENED WIDE

1670
01:10:34,330 --> 01:10:36,031
-Please have some.
-Yes.

1671
01:10:36,098 --> 01:10:37,900
You were still talking, so…

1672
01:10:37,967 --> 01:10:40,002
I'll put it in now.

1673
01:10:40,069 --> 01:10:42,871
Chef Edward takes a picture.

1674
01:10:42,938 --> 01:10:46,575
He must find it odd
to see him eat it like this.

1675
01:10:46,642 --> 01:10:51,413
Kim Poong's Dopamine Poongly Charged.

1676
01:10:51,480 --> 01:10:55,184
-He's chewing like he's not sure.
-He's tilting his head.

1677
01:10:55,251 --> 01:10:58,220
He's chewing like he isn't sure.

1678
01:10:58,287 --> 01:11:00,256
There's gum in here. What is this?

1679
01:11:00,322 --> 01:11:01,156
It's <i>kirimochi</i>.

1680
01:11:01,223 --> 01:11:04,994
-It's <i>kirimochi</i>?
-Yes, you like <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1681
01:11:05,060 --> 01:11:08,030
-This gum adds some fun.
-Doesn't it?

1682
01:11:08,097 --> 01:11:09,398
-There's rice cake?
-Yes.

1683
01:11:09,465 --> 01:11:11,834
-But it's not spicy.
-It looked spicy.

1684
01:11:11,900 --> 01:11:13,936
It stings just a little. It's not spicy.

1685
01:11:14,003 --> 01:11:15,671
It looked really spicy
when he put everything in.

1686
01:11:15,738 --> 01:11:19,408
It looked really strong
because of his bright red color,

1687
01:11:19,475 --> 01:11:20,943
but it was seasoned perfectly.

1688
01:11:21,010 --> 01:11:23,178
-Why don't we try some too?
-Yes.

1689
01:11:23,245 --> 01:11:24,680
ARTIST POONG'S
DOPAMINE POONGLY CHARGED

1690
01:11:24,747 --> 01:11:27,483
-The potato.
-I can smell the <i>mala</i> right away.

1691
01:11:27,549 --> 01:11:29,685
The rice cake was the key.

1692
01:11:29,752 --> 01:11:30,986
I can taste shrimp.

1693
01:11:31,053 --> 01:11:34,623
I think the texture is better
because you threw it in at the end.

1694
01:11:34,690 --> 01:11:36,759
It's firm and nice.

1695
01:11:36,825 --> 01:11:39,328
-It's seasoned perfectly.
-The rice cake's nice.

1696
01:11:39,395 --> 01:11:43,098
I got to experience Artist Poong's dish
for the first time in a while.

1697
01:11:43,165 --> 01:11:46,168
When I saw it in front of me,
it killed my pride a little.

1698
01:11:46,235 --> 01:11:49,772
My mouth began to water
because of the smell.

1699
01:11:49,838 --> 01:11:53,342
-Did you hate yourself?
-Was I reacting to his dish?

1700
01:11:54,610 --> 01:11:56,312
You hated yourself for that.

1701
01:11:56,378 --> 01:12:00,716
Chef Edward, what do you think?
You kept eating everything.

1702
01:12:00,783 --> 01:12:02,851
-It's delicious, but it hurts my tummy.
-Your tummy?

1703
01:12:02,918 --> 01:12:06,455
It hurts his tummy!

1704
01:12:06,522 --> 01:12:07,856
It's delicious yet painful.

1705
01:12:07,923 --> 01:12:11,593
-It's too spicy.
-It was too spicy for Chef Edward.

1706
01:12:11,660 --> 01:12:15,064
If he were the judge,
you would've been disqualified.

1707
01:12:15,130 --> 01:12:17,433
Let's taste Chef Eun-yeong's dish too.

1708
01:12:17,499 --> 01:12:19,001
-Gosh.
-Mmm.

1709
01:12:19,068 --> 01:12:21,603
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
HAPPY BASI-DAY

1710
01:12:21,670 --> 01:12:23,172
What did we eat just before?

1711
01:12:23,238 --> 01:12:25,107
I don't remember.

1712
01:12:25,174 --> 01:12:31,213
She coated it with sugar
so ice cream won't seep out as it melts.

1713
01:12:31,280 --> 01:12:36,885
I felt the moist inside, soft ice cream,
and the crunch on the outside at once.

1714
01:12:36,952 --> 01:12:38,387
It's refreshing and crunchy.

1715
01:12:40,689 --> 01:12:42,958
-I see.
-It was his favorite.

1716
01:12:43,025 --> 01:12:47,896
Also, Team Culinary Class Wars
need to win at least once.

1717
01:12:47,963 --> 01:12:50,699
I see. You're asking for a favor.

1718
01:12:50,766 --> 01:12:53,569
-Why do you keep staring at me?
-Please.

1719
01:12:53,635 --> 01:12:56,138
-Wait, say something, Master Yeon-bok!
-Well, she won.

1720
01:12:56,205 --> 01:12:58,974
I pick the one I liked, right?

1721
01:12:59,041 --> 01:13:00,609
But you won't be shaken.

1722
01:13:00,676 --> 01:13:02,378
I enjoyed both, though.

1723
01:13:02,444 --> 01:13:05,447
-It would've been great as a set.
-Right? If these two came out together.

1724
01:13:05,514 --> 01:13:08,350
-Eat this first, then the dessert.
-That'd be amazing.

1725
01:13:08,417 --> 01:13:10,185
The rice cake inside

1726
01:13:10,252 --> 01:13:13,789
mixed well with the sauce
thanks to its glutinous nature.

1727
01:13:13,856 --> 01:13:15,824
It almost tasted like <i>sujebi</i>,

1728
01:13:15,891 --> 01:13:19,061
but the kind that covered all your mouth.

1729
01:13:19,128 --> 01:13:21,296
-Like this.
-Yes, like this.

1730
01:13:21,363 --> 01:13:23,332
Do you have to do that before me?

1731
01:13:23,399 --> 01:13:25,768
THE GESTURE TO REMEMBER FOR LIFE

1732
01:13:25,834 --> 01:13:29,271
This time, I'd have no excuses to make
even if I lost this round.

1733
01:13:29,338 --> 01:13:32,040
It was perfect to my taste too.

1734
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:34,843
But now, you must make the choice.

1735
01:13:34,910 --> 01:13:38,046
Please choose just one dish that gave you…

1736
01:13:38,113 --> 01:13:40,549
-Yes.
-…more dopamine than the other.

1737
01:13:40,616 --> 01:13:44,153
The returning chefs have won
all three rounds consecutively.

1738
01:13:44,219 --> 01:13:47,322
Let's find out
who won the final round.

1739
01:13:47,389 --> 01:13:50,092
Chimchakman, make your choice.

1740
01:13:50,159 --> 01:13:51,860
Kim Poong is number one,

1741
01:13:51,927 --> 01:13:53,695
Park Eun-yeong is number two.

1742
01:13:53,762 --> 01:13:56,565
Please make your decision
and press the button.

1743
01:13:57,433 --> 01:13:59,902
-I did.
-He picked one.

1744
01:13:59,968 --> 01:14:01,703
There is a lot at stake here.

1745
01:14:01,770 --> 01:14:05,274
-Lee Yeon-bok and Lu Chinglai's honor.
-Yes.

1746
01:14:05,340 --> 01:14:07,743
And the honor between
the returning chef and the new chefs.

1747
01:14:07,810 --> 01:14:11,914
Kim Poong and Park Eun-yeong are
also fighting for the honor of their name.

1748
01:14:11,980 --> 01:14:15,617
Let us confirm the result
of today's final battle! Let's see.

1749
01:14:16,185 --> 01:14:19,555
A mouthwatering dopamine explosion.

1750
01:14:19,621 --> 01:14:23,392
Kim Poong's dish
versus Chef Park Eun-yeong's dish.

1751
01:14:23,459 --> 01:14:26,562
-Who knows who'll win?
-It was for Lee Yeon-bok and Lu Chinglai.

1752
01:14:26,628 --> 01:14:30,065
Who did Chimchakman choose?

1753
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:34,303
Which dish gave him more dopamine? It is…

1754
01:14:34,369 --> 01:14:35,204
It is…

1755
01:14:38,040 --> 01:14:39,041
It is…

1756
01:14:39,107 --> 01:14:40,509
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

1757
01:14:40,576 --> 01:14:43,579
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
HAPPY BASI-DAY WINS

1758
01:14:44,346 --> 01:14:46,748
Chef Eun-yeong wins!

1759
01:14:46,815 --> 01:14:48,750
Chef Edward gives a standing ovation.

1760
01:14:48,817 --> 01:14:50,819
A standing ovation.

1761
01:14:50,886 --> 01:14:52,554
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR VICTORY

1762
01:14:52,621 --> 01:14:57,459
Chef Eun-yeong saved the face
of Team Culinary Class Wars.

1763
01:14:57,526 --> 01:15:01,096
She becomes the final winner.

1764
01:15:01,163 --> 01:15:03,332
Both dishes were delicious,

1765
01:15:03,398 --> 01:15:06,635
but you told me to consider
which one fits the topic better.

1766
01:15:07,603 --> 01:15:09,371
I get why I have too many gold teeth.

1767
01:15:10,739 --> 01:15:11,874
-I see.
-Yes.

1768
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:15,444
I went back to page one
and wondered what gave me dopamine,

1769
01:15:15,511 --> 01:15:19,448
and Chef Eun-yeong's dish was
a little closer to my dopamine hit.

1770
01:15:19,515 --> 01:15:21,183
You must be disappointed, Poong.

1771
01:15:22,017 --> 01:15:23,285
I'm not disappointed.

1772
01:15:23,352 --> 01:15:25,487
My fighting spirit is now on fire.

1773
01:15:27,089 --> 01:15:29,358
I can sense my blood boiling now.

1774
01:15:29,424 --> 01:15:32,694
Yes, the more you're trampled on,
the stronger you get.

1775
01:15:32,761 --> 01:15:33,729
This is exhilarating.

1776
01:15:36,732 --> 01:15:37,633
-Yes.
-Yes.

1777
01:15:37,699 --> 01:15:41,036
But we had a friendly and fun time.

1778
01:15:43,071 --> 01:15:45,240
I see.

1779
01:15:45,307 --> 01:15:48,644
The new chefs had their first win.

1780
01:15:48,710 --> 01:15:51,113
Here's a star for you, Chef Eun-yeong.

1781
01:15:51,179 --> 01:15:54,049
You seized the first victory
among the new chefs!

1782
01:15:54,116 --> 01:15:57,019
Congratulations. Chef Eun-yeong did it.

1783
01:15:57,085 --> 01:16:00,322
These are actors
you rarely see on a variety show.

1784
01:16:00,389 --> 01:16:02,524
Please welcome
Lee Hee-jun and Song Joong-ki!

1785
01:16:02,591 --> 01:16:04,359
-It's been ten years.
-Ten years?

1786
01:16:04,426 --> 01:16:06,461
I really wanted to meet this person.

1787
01:16:06,528 --> 01:16:07,663
A celebrity for Joong-ki.

1788
01:16:07,729 --> 01:16:11,500
I'm too nervous to look at Napoli Matfia.

1789
01:16:11,567 --> 01:16:14,069
I heard Team Culinary Class Wars
didn't do so well.

1790
01:16:14,136 --> 01:16:15,237
I couldn't take it.

1791
01:16:15,304 --> 01:16:16,772
It's reassuring to have him.

1792
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,107
I wanted to fight the legendary chef.

1793
01:16:19,174 --> 01:16:20,309
I won for no reason.

1794
01:16:20,375 --> 01:16:22,544
THE BATTLE OF THE CENTURY WILL
CHANGE THE COURSE OF CHINESE CUISINE

1795
01:16:22,611 --> 01:16:25,414
Joong-ki is taking a video.

1796
01:16:25,480 --> 01:16:27,316
I thought he said he'd stop doing this.

1797
01:16:27,382 --> 01:16:28,550
You can feel it.

1798
01:16:28,617 --> 01:16:30,686
How can my fridge
put something like this together?

1799
01:16:30,752 --> 01:16:32,888
This was the best thing I did this year.

1800
01:16:32,955 --> 01:16:34,823
Deciding to come to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1801
01:16:35,857 --> 01:16:36,725
AND…

1802
01:16:36,792 --> 01:16:39,895
I'm suddenly so touched.

1803
01:16:39,962 --> 01:16:41,797
Yes, his eyes are getting teary.

1804
01:16:41,863 --> 01:16:44,399
This was so…

1805
01:16:59,815 --> 01:17:04,820
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
